T* (                "markdown": "About 400 years ago, the scientist **Galileo** claimed something strange: without air ) Tj
T* (pushing back, a heavy thing and a light thing should fall **together** -- gravity speeds them up equally.\\n\\nOn Earth, ) Tj
T* (air ruins the test. A feather flutters because air catches it like a tiny parachute.\\n\\nBut the Moon has **no air at ) Tj
T* (all**. In 1971, astronaut **David Scott** stood on the Moon holding a hammer in one hand and a falcon feather in the ) Tj
T* (other. He let go of both at the same time... and they hit the dust **at exactly the same moment**. Galileo was right -- ) Tj
T* (it just took 400 years and a trip to the Moon to film the proof.") Tj
ET
endstream
endobj
