T* (              "title": "Why does this matter?",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Look at the Moon every night for a month and draw what you see. Your drawings will show a ) Tj
T* (thin smile, then a half circle, then a glowing full disc, then back to a sliver -- and then it starts over.\\n\\nLong ) Tj
T* (before clocks and calendars, people used these shapes to **count time**. The word *month* even comes from *Moon*! ) Tj
T* (Farmers planted by it, sailors planned voyages by it, and many holidays around the world are still set by the Moon's ) Tj
T* (shape today.\\n\\nBut the Moon is a solid ball of rock. Rock doesn't melt away and regrow each month. The changing shapes ) Tj
T* (-- called **phases** -- are one of the sky's greatest illusions, and you're about to see through it.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
