T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "A common mix-up: many people think the dark part of the Moon is **Earth's shadow**. It ) Tj
T* (isn't! During phases, Earth's shadow is nowhere near the Moon. The dark part is simply the Moon's own **night side** -- ) Tj
T* (the half facing away from the Sun.\\n\\nEarth's shadow does occasionally sweep across the Moon, but that is a special ) Tj
T* (event called a **lunar eclipse**. It can only happen at a Full Moon, when Sun, Earth, and Moon line up almost perfectly ) Tj
T* (-- and the Moon often turns an eerie copper-red as Earth's atmosphere bends red sunlight into the shadow. Eclipses are ) Tj
T* (rare; phases happen every single night. Different machinery entirely!") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
