T* (                  "Half of the Moon is always lit by the Sun -- phases are about which part of that lit half we see.",) Tj
T* (                  "The Moon orbits Earth about every 29.5 days, giving one full cycle of phases.",) Tj
T* (                  "Order: New -> Crescent -> First Quarter -> Gibbous -> Full -> Gibbous -> Last Quarter -> Crescent -> ) Tj
T* (New.",) Tj
T* (                  "Waxing = growing toward Full. Waning = shrinking toward New.",) Tj
T* (                  "The dark part of the Moon is its own night side -- not Earth's shadow.") Tj
