T* (              "kind": "DEEPER_DIVE",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Deeper dive: why we never see the far side",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "The Moon's spin and its orbit are perfectly matched -- one spin per one trip around Earth. ) Tj
T* (Scientists call this **tidal locking**, and it is no coincidence.\\n\\nBillions of years ago the Moon spun faster. But ) Tj
T* (Earth's gravity pulls a little harder on the Moon's near side than its far side, stretching it slightly. That constant ) Tj
T* (stretching acted like a gentle brake, slowing the Moon's spin over millions of years until it locked: now it rotates ) Tj
T* (exactly once per orbit, forever showing us the same face.\\n\\nThe same brake is working on Earth right now -- the Moon's ) Tj
T* (pull is slowing our spin too. Earth's day grows about **2 milliseconds longer every century**. Dinosaurs lived days that) Tj
T* ( were only about 23 hours long!") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "SUMMARY",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Mission summary",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "takeaways": [) Tj
T* (                  "A day-night cycle on the Moon lasts about 29.5 Earth days -- two weeks of light, two weeks of dark.",) Tj
T* (                  "The Moon has no air: the daytime sky is black, and there is no sound, wind, or rain.",) Tj
T* (                  "With no air blanket, temperatures swing from about +120 degC to -130 degC.",) Tj
T* (                  "No weather means footprints and tracks can last for millions of years.",) Tj
T* (                  "The Moon is tidally locked -- the same side always faces Earth.") Tj
T* (                ],) Tj
T* (                "formulas": [) Tj
T* (                  {) Tj
T* (                    "label": "Lunar day",) Tj
T* (                    "tex": "1 \\\\text{ Moon day} \\\\approx 29.5 \\\\text{ Earth days}") Tj
T* (                  }) Tj
T* (                ]) Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            }) Tj
T* (          ],) Tj
T* (          "questions": [) Tj
