T* (              "title": "Deeper dive: how fast is falling?",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Scientists measured Earth's gravity precisely. Near the ground, every falling object gains ) Tj
T* (about **9.8 meters per second of speed, every second** \(when air isn't interfering\). We call this number **g**.\\n\\nAfter) Tj
T* ( 1 second of falling: about 10 m/s. After 2 seconds: about 20 m/s. After 3 seconds: about 30 m/s -- already highway ) Tj
T* (speed!\\n\\nOn the Moon, g is only about **1.6** -- which is exactly why everything there fell in dreamy slow motion. When) Tj
T* ( you're older you'll write this as the famous formula **v = g*t** \(speed = gravity x time\). You've already discovered ) Tj
T* (what it means.") Tj
