(              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Here is one of the strangest true facts in physics: **you cannot push something without it ) Tj
T* (pushing you back.**\\n\\nPush hard against a wall -- feel your hands being pushed back? Step off a skateboard by pushing ) Tj
T* (it backward, and *you* glide forward while the board shoots back. A swimmer pushes water backward; the water pushes the ) Tj
T* (swimmer forward. Even a rocket works this way: it hurls hot gas down, and the gas pushes the rocket up. Rockets don't ) Tj
T* (push against the ground or the air -- which is why they work perfectly in empty space.\\n\\nIsaac Newton wrote this down ) Tj
T* (about 340 years ago: *for every action there is an equal and opposite reaction.* You'll meet Newton again and again on ) Tj
T* (this journey -- he basically wrote the rulebook for moving things.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
