T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "How do we *know* Earth spins, rather than the Sun circling us? For centuries no one could ) Tj
T* (prove it directly. Then in 1851, French physicist **L?on Foucault** hung a heavy ball on a 67-meter wire from the ) Tj
T* (ceiling of the Panth?on in Paris and set it swinging.\\n\\nA swinging pendulum keeps its swing-direction fixed in space. ) Tj
T* (Yet hour by hour, the crowd watched the pendulum's path slowly turn relative to the floor... because the **floor -- the ) Tj
T* (Earth -- was turning underneath it.** People could literally watch the planet rotate.\\n\\nFoucault pendulums still swing ) Tj
T* (in science museums all over the world today. Find one, watch it for an hour, and you'll see the Earth turn with your own) Tj
T* ( eyes.") Tj
