T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "In 1654, German scientist **Otto von Guericke** staged one of the greatest demos in ) Tj
T* (history. He fitted two copper half-spheres together, pumped the air **out** of the inside... and invited two teams of ) Tj
T* (horses to pull them apart.\\n\\nSixteen horses heaved. The spheres held.\\n\\nNothing was gluing them -- nothing was *inside) Tj
T* ( at all*. The atmosphere outside was simply pressing the halves together with tonnes of force, with no inside air to ) Tj
T* (push back. When von Guericke opened a valve and let air hiss back in, the spheres fell apart in his hands.\\n\\nThe ) Tj
T* ('Magdeburg hemispheres' proved the invisible ocean is mighty. Every vacuum cleaner, suction cup, and drinking straw is a) Tj
T* ( tiny tribute to those sixteen confused horses.") Tj
