(            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONTEXT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Why does this matter?",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Weather decides whether your soccer game happens, what you wear, and what farmers can grow.) Tj
T* ( Severe weather -- storms, hurricanes, heat waves -- shapes lives around the world. Forecasting it accurately saves ) Tj
T* (thousands of lives every year.\\n\\nAnd remarkably, almost all of it -- every breeze, cloud, and thunderstorm -- is ) Tj
T* (powered by a single engine: **the Sun heating the Earth unevenly**. Master that one idea, and the daily weather report ) Tj
T* (transforms from mysterious jargon \('a low-pressure system is moving in...'\) into a story you can actually follow.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONCEPT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "The big idea",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Three gears make the weather engine turn:\\n\\n**Gear 1: The Sun heats Earth unevenly.** ) Tj
T* (Sunlight warms dark pavement faster than grass, land faster than the sea, and the equator far more than the poles. The ) Tj
T* (air sitting above warm ground gets warmed too -- Earth's surface acts like a stove burner under the ocean of ) Tj
T* (air.\\n\\n**Gear 2: Warm air rises, cool air sinks.** When air warms, its molecules zip around faster and spread out -- ) Tj
T* (the air becomes **less dense** \(lighter for its size\), so it floats upward through the cooler air around it, exactly ) Tj
T* (like a bubble rising in water or a hot-air balloon lifting off. Cool, denser air sinks to take its place. This endless ) Tj
T* (vertical loop is called **convection**.\\n\\n**Gear 3: Wind is air rushing from high pressure to low pressure.** Where air) Tj
T* ( rises, less air is left pressing on the ground -- a **low-pressure** zone. Where air sinks and piles up, pressure runs ) Tj
T* (**high**. And air, like a crowd leaving a stadium, always flows from the packed place to the empty place: **from high ) Tj
T* (pressure toward low pressure. That horizontal flow is wind.** Bigger pressure difference = faster wind. A hurricane is ) Tj
T* (simply this engine running at terrifying full throttle around an extreme low.\\n\\n**See all three gears at the beach.** ) Tj
T* (On a sunny afternoon, land heats up faster than the sea. Air over the land warms and rises \(low pressure on land\); ) Tj
T* (cooler, heavier sea air slides in to replace it. That's the famous afternoon **sea breeze**, blowing from water to land.) Tj
T* ( At night the engine reverses: land cools quickly, the sea stays warm, and a gentle **land breeze** drifts out to sea. ) Tj
T* (One beach, a complete weather system in miniature.\\n\\n**Bonus gear: rising air builds clouds.** Rising warm air carries ) Tj
T* (invisible water vapor upward. High up, it cools, and the vapor condenses into countless droplets -- a **cloud**. Pile up) Tj
T* ( enough rising, moist air and you get rain. So next time you see a towering summer cloud, you're watching Gear 2 in ) Tj
T* (action, kilometers tall.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "SIMULATION",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Try it: breeze machine",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "simId": "sea-breeze",) Tj
T* (                "intro": "Heat the day with the sunshine slider and watch the convection loop spin up: warm air rising ) Tj
T* (over land, cool sea air sliding in underneath. Then switch to night and watch the whole engine run backwards.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "WORKED_EXAMPLES",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Worked examples",) Tj
