T* (                  {) Tj
T* (                    "title": "Which way does the flag point?",) Tj
T* (                    "problem": "It's a hot, sunny afternoon at the beach. Which way does the breeze blow -- from sea to ) Tj
T* (land, or land to sea?",) Tj
T* (                    "steps": [) Tj
T* (                      "Sun heats land faster than water; air over land warms and rises.",) Tj
T* (                      "Rising air leaves lower pressure over the land.",) Tj
T* (                      "Cooler, denser sea air flows in toward that low pressure.") Tj
T* (                    ],) Tj
T* (                    "answer": "From sea to land -- the classic afternoon sea breeze. Flags on the beach flap inland.") Tj
T* (                  },) Tj
T* (                  {) Tj
T* (                    "title": "The radiator loop",) Tj
T* (                    "problem": "A heater sits under a window on one side of a room, yet the whole room warms up. Trace ) Tj
T* (the air's journey.",) Tj
T* (                    "steps": [) Tj
T* (                      "Air touching the heater warms, becomes less dense, and rises to the ceiling.",) Tj
T* (                      "It drifts across the ceiling, cooling as it goes, then sinks on the far side.",) Tj
T* (                      "Cool floor-level air flows back toward the heater to be warmed in turn -- a convection loop.") Tj
T* (                    ],) Tj
T* (                    "answer": "A circulating loop: up at the heater, across the ceiling, down the far wall, back along ) Tj
T* (the floor. The room is a tiny atmosphere.") Tj
T* (                  },) Tj
T* (                  {) Tj
T* (                    "title": "Reading the forecast",) Tj
T* (                    "problem": "The forecaster says: 'A strong low-pressure system arrives tomorrow.' Should you expect ) Tj
T* (calm sunshine or wind and possible rain -- and why?",) Tj
T* (                    "steps": [) Tj
T* (                      "A low means air is rising there, and surrounding air rushes inward -- that's wind.",) Tj
T* (                      "Rising air cools, and its moisture condenses into clouds.",) Tj
T* (                      "Lots of rising, moist air often means rain.") Tj
T* (                    ],) Tj
