T* (              "kind": "DEEPER_DIVE",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Deeper dive: the wind that circles the world",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Scale the beach breeze up to the whole planet. The equator is Earth's permanent 'hot land,') Tj
T* ( the poles its permanent 'cool sea.' Giant convection loops form, with warm equatorial air rising and flowing poleward ) Tj
T* (high above, while cooler air returns along the surface.\\n\\nBut there's a twist -- literally. Because the **Earth is ) Tj
T* (spinning** \(remember the great carousel?\), these planet-sized winds get deflected sideways as they travel, an effect ) Tj
T* (called the **Coriolis effect**. The result: steady wind highways like the **trade winds**, which sailors rode west ) Tj
T* (across the Atlantic for centuries, and the **jet streams** -- rivers of air 10 km up, screaming along at 200+ km/h, ) Tj
T* (which is why your flight east is faster than your flight west.\\n\\nEvery local breeze belongs to this single, ) Tj
T* (planet-wide, Sun-powered, spin-twisted machine. Meteorologists model it with supercomputers; you now understand its ) Tj
T* (gears.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "SUMMARY",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Mission summary",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "takeaways": [) Tj
T* (                  "The Sun heats Earth's surface unevenly -- that's the energy source for all weather.",) Tj
T* (                  "Warm air is less dense and rises; cool air is denser and sinks \(convection\).",) Tj
T* (                  "Rising air creates low pressure; sinking, piling air creates high pressure.",) Tj
T* (                  "Wind is air flowing from high pressure to low pressure -- bigger difference, stronger wind.",) Tj
T* (                  "Sea breeze by day, land breeze by night; rising moist air builds clouds and rain.") Tj
T* (                ],) Tj
T* (                "formulas": [) Tj
T* (                  {) Tj
T* (                    "label": "Wind rule",) Tj
T* (                    "tex": "\\\\text{wind: } P_{high} \\\\longrightarrow P_{low}") Tj
T* (                  }) Tj
