T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Change the atmosphere, change the sky.\\n\\n**Mars** has an ultra-thin atmosphere of carbon ) Tj
T* (dioxide laced with fine rusty dust. The dust scatters light differently than gas molecules do: the Martian daytime sky ) Tj
T* (glows a **butterscotch tan** -- and at sunset, the area around the Sun turns **blue**. Mars has blue sunsets! NASA's ) Tj
T* (rovers have photographed them.\\n\\n**Titan**, Saturn's giant moon, is wrapped in a thick orange smog of nitrogen and ) Tj
T* (hydrocarbons -- its sky is a deep orange murk where the Sun is just a brighter patch.\\n\\nAstronomers now study the ) Tj
T* (colors of skies on **exoplanets** -- worlds orbiting other stars -- by analyzing starlight that filters through their ) Tj
T* (atmospheres. The same Rayleigh physics you just learned is one of the tools being used, right now, to search distant ) Tj
T* (skies for signs of life.") Tj
