T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "DEEPER_DIVE",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Deeper dive: Galileo's leap of imagination",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "For 2,000 years people believed Aristotle: that things stop moving because stopping is ) Tj
T* (their natural state, and motion needs a constant push to continue.\\n\\n**Galileo** doubted it. He rolled balls down one ) Tj
T* (ramp and up another, and noticed the ball always tried to climb back to its starting height. Make the second ramp ) Tj
T* (gentler, and the ball rolled farther to reach that height. So what if the second ramp were perfectly flat and ) Tj
T* (frictionless? Galileo reasoned the ball would roll **forever**, never finding its height.\\n\\nHe couldn't build a ) Tj
T* (frictionless surface -- but he could imagine one. That leap, later sharpened by Newton, overturned two millennia of ) Tj
T* (physics: motion doesn't need a cause; *changes* in motion do. Centuries later, spacecraft coasting silently between the ) Tj
T* (planets are the proof Galileo never got to see.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "SUMMARY",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Mission summary",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "takeaways": [) Tj
T* (                  "A force is a push or pull, measured in newtons \(N\), with size and direction.",) Tj
T* (                  "Net force is what's left after all forces combine. Balanced \(net = 0\) means no change in motion.",) Tj
T* (                  "Inertia: objects resist changes to their motion. Things stop because of friction, not 'naturally'.",) Tj
T* (                  "The same force changes a light object's motion more than a heavy one's \(less mass, less inertia\).",) Tj
T* (                  "Forces come in equal, opposite pairs -- push the wall and it pushes you back.") Tj
T* (                ],) Tj
T* (                "formulas": [) Tj
T* (                  {) Tj
T* (                    "label": "Net force",) Tj
T* (                    "tex": "F_{net} = \\\\sum F \\\\quad \(F_{net}=0 \\\\Rightarrow \\\\text{motion unchanged}\)") Tj
T* (                  }) Tj
T* (                ]) Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            }) Tj
