T* (              "title": "Deeper dive: 'Give me a place to stand'",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "The ancient Greek genius **Archimedes** understood levers so deeply he reportedly boasted, ) Tj
T* (*'Give me a place to stand and a lever long enough, and I will move the Earth.'*\\n\\nHe wasn't entirely joking. With a ) Tj
T* (long enough lever and a fulcrum, the *force* needed to lift even the Earth would be small -- though you'd have to move ) Tj
T* (your end of the lever an absurd, cosmic distance, for an unimaginable length of time. The force shrinks; the distance ) Tj
T* (explodes. The deal always holds.\\n\\nArchimedes turned this insight into war machines, water screws still used for ) Tj
T* (irrigation today, and the foundations of mechanics. Every robotic arm, crane, and excavator is a descendant of his ) Tj
T* (lever.") Tj
