T* (                "takeaways": [) Tj
T* (                  "Simple machines change a force's size or direction to make work easier.",) Tj
T* (                  "They never give free energy: less force always costs more distance.",) Tj
T* (                  "Mechanical advantage MA = load / effort tells you how many times the force is multiplied.",) Tj
T* (                  "Lever, inclined plane, pulley, wheel-and-axle, wedge, and screw are the six classics.",) Tj
T* (                  "Friction means real machines help a bit less than the ideal -- lubrication recovers some.") Tj
