T* (              "kind": "HERO",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "scene": "sun",) Tj
T* (                "headline": "The Universe's Unspendable Currency",) Tj
T* (                "sub": "Energy can hide as motion, height, heat, light, or chemical fuel -- and flip between them ) Tj
T* (endlessly. But the grand total never changes. Not once, anywhere, ever.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONTEXT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Why does this matter?",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Sunlight becomes plant sugar becomes the energy in your muscles becomes the motion of a ) Tj
T* (thrown ball becomes heat when it lands. Energy is the single thread running through every event in the universe.\\n\\nThe ) Tj
T* (deepest law in all of science is that this thread is **never cut**: energy is only ever **transformed** from one form to) Tj
T* ( another, never created or destroyed. Understand the forms of energy and the law that ties them together, and you hold ) Tj
T* (the master key to physics, chemistry, biology, and engineering alike.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONCEPT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "The big idea",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "**Energy is the ability to do work** -- to make things move, heat up, or change. Like work,) Tj
T* ( it's measured in **joules**. It comes in many forms:\\n\\n- **Kinetic energy** -- the energy of **motion**. Anything ) Tj
T* (moving has it: a thrown ball, flowing water, a zooming spacecraft. More speed or more mass means more kinetic energy.\\n-) Tj
T* ( **Potential energy** -- **stored** energy, waiting to be released. A raised hammer has **gravitational** potential ) Tj
T* (energy \(height\); a stretched spring or drawn bow has **elastic** potential energy; food and fuel hold **chemical** ) Tj
T* (potential energy in their bonds.\\n- **Thermal energy** -- the energy of jiggling particles; we feel it as heat.\\n- ) Tj
ET
