(**Light \(radiant\) energy** -- carried by light, like the sunlight crossing space.\\n- **Electrical energy** -- carried by) Tj
T* ( moving charges through a wire.\\n- **Sound energy** -- carried by vibrations through a material.\\n\\n**Energy ) Tj
T* (transforms.** Almost everything interesting is one form of energy turning into another:\\n\\n- A roller coaster trades ) Tj
T* (**gravitational potential** \(at the top\) for **kinetic** \(at the bottom\), then back again on the next hill.\\n- A ) Tj
T* (flashlight turns **chemical** \(battery\) -> **electrical** -> **light** and **thermal**.\\n- A plant turns **light** -> ) Tj
T* (**chemical** \(sugar\). You eat it and turn **chemical** -> **kinetic** \(movement\) and **thermal** \(body heat\).\\n\\n**The ) Tj
T* (law of conservation of energy:** in any change, **the total energy stays the same**. Energy is never created from ) Tj
T* (nothing and never truly destroyed -- only moved and reshaped. When a bouncing ball finally stops, its energy didn't ) Tj
T* (vanish; it spread out as heat and sound. That's also why a true 'perpetual motion machine' is impossible: there's no way) Tj
T* ( to get out more energy than you put in.\\n\\n**Friction is energy's escape hatch.** In real machines and motions, some ) Tj
T* (energy always 'leaks' into thermal energy \(heat\) and sound, spreading out where it's hard to use again. The total is ) Tj
T* (still conserved -- but the useful part shrinks. That's why nothing is 100% efficient.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "WORKED_EXAMPLES",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Worked examples",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "examples": [) Tj
T* (                  {) Tj
T* (                    "title": "Roller-coaster energy swap",) Tj
T* (                    "problem": "A coaster car has 50,000 J of gravitational potential energy at the top of a hill. ) Tj
T* (Ignoring friction, what is its kinetic energy at the bottom?",) Tj
T* (                    "steps": [) Tj
T* (                      "Energy is conserved: the total stays 50,000 J.",) Tj
T* (                      "At the bottom, the height \(potential\) is gone -- converted to motion.",) Tj
T* (                      "So all 50,000 J has become kinetic energy.") Tj
T* (                    ],) Tj
T* (                    "answer": "50,000 J of kinetic energy. The potential energy of height turned entirely into the ) Tj
T* (energy of motion. \(Real coasters lose a little to friction, so it's slightly less.\)") Tj
T* (                  },) Tj
T* (                  {) Tj
T* (                    "title": "Trace the flashlight",) Tj
T* (                    "problem": "List the chain of energy transformations when you switch on a battery flashlight.",) Tj
T* (                    "steps": [) Tj
T* (                      "The battery stores chemical potential energy.",) Tj
T* (                      "Switching on lets it flow as electrical energy through the bulb.",) Tj
T* (                      "The bulb converts that to light energy -- and some thermal energy \(it gets warm\).") Tj
T* (                    ],) Tj
T* (                    "answer": "Chemical -> electrical -> light + thermal. The warmth you feel is the 'leaked' part -- ) Tj
T* (proof no transformation is perfectly efficient.") Tj
T* (                  },) Tj
T* (                  {) Tj
T* (                    "title": "Where did the bounce go?",) Tj
T* (                    "problem": "A dropped ball bounces a little lower each time, then stops. Energy is conserved, so ) Tj
T* (where did its energy go?",) Tj
T* (                    "steps": [) Tj
T* (                      "Each bounce, some kinetic energy converts to thermal energy and sound.",) Tj
T* (                      "The ball and floor warm up slightly; you hear the 'thud'.",) Tj
T* (                      "After many bounces, all the original energy has spread out as heat and sound.") Tj
T* (                    ],) Tj
T* (                    "answer": "It became thermal energy \(heat\) and sound, spread into the ball, floor, and air. Nothing ) Tj
T* (was destroyed -- just scattered into hard-to-use forms.") Tj
T* (                  }) Tj
T* (                ]) Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
