T* (              "kind": "DEEPER_DIVE",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Deeper dive: the law that survived everything",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Conservation of energy is one of the most tested ideas in science -- and it has never once ) Tj
T* (failed. Whenever it seemed to break, physicists discovered a hidden form of energy rather than abandon the law.\\n\\nIn ) Tj
T* (the 1930s, certain radioactive decays seemed to lose a little energy. Rather than give up conservation, **Wolfgang ) Tj
T* (Pauli** boldly predicted an invisible, nearly massless particle carrying the missing energy away. Decades later the ) Tj
T* (**neutrino** was found -- exactly as conservation demanded. Trillions are streaming through your body right ) Tj
T* (now.\\n\\nEinstein deepened the law with $E = mc^2$: mass itself is a super-concentrated form of energy. The Sun shines by) Tj
T* ( converting a tiny bit of its mass into the light that, eight minutes later, warms your face. Energy bookkeeping, on a ) Tj
ET
