T* (                "markdown": "When an earthquake strikes, it sends out **seismic waves** -- both transverse and ) Tj
T* (longitudinal -- that race through the planet. Networks of sensors around the world catch them.\\n\\nHere's the clever ) Tj
T* (part: different waves travel at different speeds and bend as they pass through materials of different density, exactly ) Tj
T* (like light refracting. By timing when each wave arrives and how it bent, geologists have **mapped the inside of the ) Tj
T* (Earth** -- a place no drill will ever reach. That's how we know Earth has a solid inner core, a liquid outer core, and a) Tj
T* ( thick rocky mantle: we read it in the waves.\\n\\nThe same trick, aimed at the sky instead of the ground, lets ) Tj
T* (astronomers read the insides of stars from the way they ring and pulse -- a field called *asteroseismology*.") Tj
