T* (                      "Crossing that boundary, the light changes speed and bends -- refraction.",) Tj
T* (                      "Your brain assumes light travelled straight, so the straw appears displaced.") Tj
T* (                    ],) Tj
T* (                    "answer": "Refraction. Light bends as it leaves the water, shifting the straw's apparent position so) Tj
T* ( it looks broken at the surface.") Tj
T* (                  },) Tj
