T* (                      "A bigger mirror has more area to catch light.",) Tj
T* (                      "More light gathered means fainter, farther objects become visible.") Tj
T* (                    ],) Tj
T* (                    "answer": "A larger mirror collects more light, revealing fainter and more distant objects -- which ) Tj
T* (is why observatories build ever-bigger mirrors.") Tj
T* (                  },) Tj
T* (                  {) Tj
T* (                    "title": "Light from the past",) Tj
T* (                    "problem": "A star is 100 light-years away. What does it mean to say we 'see it as it was 100 years ) Tj
T* (ago'?",) Tj
T* (                    "steps": [) Tj
