T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "When the **Hubble Space Telescope** launched in 1990, its images came back blurry. ) Tj
T* (Engineers were horrified: the main mirror had been ground to the wrong shape by an amount thinner than a human hair -- a) Tj
T* ( flaw in its curvature that smeared every star.\\n\\nBecause the error was precisely known, opticians could design ) Tj
T* (corrective optics -- in effect, **eyeglasses for a telescope**. In 1993, astronauts flew up and installed them. Hubble ) Tj
T* (snapped into perfect focus and went on to take some of the most famous images in history.\\n\\nThe whole rescue was pure ) Tj
T* (optics: a curvature error in one mirror, cancelled by a matching curvature in another. The same physics that fixes ) Tj
T* (nearsighted eyes fixed humanity's greatest telescope.") Tj
