T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "In 1964, two engineers, **Penzias and Wilson**, were testing a sensitive radio antenna in ) Tj
T* (New Jersey. No matter where they pointed it, a faint hiss of microwave static remained. They checked everything -- even ) Tj
T* (scrubbed out pigeon droppings from the antenna. The hiss stayed.\\n\\nIt turned out they were hearing the **cosmic ) Tj
T* (microwave background**: the faint afterglow of the Big Bang itself, stretched by the universe's expansion from blinding ) Tj
T* (light into a whisper of microwaves, arriving from every direction in the sky. They had accidentally detected the ) Tj
T* (leftover heat of creation, 13.8 billion years old.\\n\\nThe discovery won the Nobel Prize and is among the strongest ) Tj
T* (evidence that the universe began in a hot, dense state. A reminder that every band of the spectrum has a story to tell ) Tj
T* (-- even the static.") Tj
