T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "DEEPER_DIVE",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Deeper dive: the engine that taught us the law",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "The science of energy and heat -- **thermodynamics** -- was born not in a lab but in the ) Tj
T* (smoke and clamor of the Industrial Revolution. Engineers building steam engines desperately wanted to know: how much ) Tj
T* (work can we squeeze from a given amount of burning coal? Is there a limit?\\n\\nIn 1824 a young French engineer, **Sadi ) Tj
T* (Carnot**, proved there is. No engine, however cleverly built, can convert all its heat into work -- there's a hard ) Tj
T* (ceiling set by the temperatures it runs between. From his analysis grew the **second law of thermodynamics** and the ) Tj
T* (concept of **entropy**.\\n\\nThe lesson echoes far beyond engines. Entropy's relentless increase is why heat won't flow ) Tj
T* (uphill on its own, why we age, and why time runs in one direction. A practical question about coal and steam led to one ) Tj
T* (of the most profound truths in all of science.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "SUMMARY",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Mission summary",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "takeaways": [) Tj
T* (                  "Energy is conserved \(total never changes\), but every real transformation leaks some as waste heat.",) Tj
T* (                  "Efficiency = useful energy out / total energy in x 100%, always less than 100%.",) Tj
T* (                  "Examples: old bulbs ~10%, car engines ~25-30%, LEDs ~80-90%.",) Tj
T* (                  "Perpetual motion machines are impossible because the 'heat tax' can never be avoided.",) Tj
T* (                  "Entropy -- the spreading of energy toward disorder -- even sets the arrow of time.") Tj
T* (                ],) Tj
T* (                "formulas": [) Tj
T* (                  {) Tj
T* (                    "label": "Efficiency",) Tj
T* (                    "tex": "\\\\text{efficiency} = \\\\frac{\\\\text{useful out}}{\\\\text{total in}} \\\\times 100\\\\%") Tj
T* (                  }) Tj
T* (                ]) Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            }) Tj
T* (          ],) Tj
T* (          "questions": [) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "scope": "CONCEPT_CHECK",) Tj
T* (              "kind": "TRUE_FALSE",) Tj
T* (              "prompt": "In a real machine, some input energy always escapes as waste heat.",) Tj
T* (              "answer": true,) Tj
T* (              "difficulty": 2,) Tj
T* (              "explanation": "Every real transformation loses some energy to low-grade heat that spreads out -- the ) Tj
T* (unavoidable 'heat tax'.") Tj
T* (            },) Tj
