T* (                "headline": "Describing Motion",) Tj
T* (                "sub": "Before we can talk about how fast or how soon, we need a precise language for where an object is) Tj
T* ( and how far it has travelled.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONTEXT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Why this matters",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Every GPS fix, every spacecraft trajectory, every self-driving car begins with the same ) Tj
T* (question: *where is it, and how has that changed?*\\n\\nIn everyday speech we use \\"distance\\" loosely. Physics needs two ) Tj
T* (distinct ideas -- **distance** and **displacement** -- because they answer different questions and, as you'll see, they ) Tj
T* (are often **not** the same number.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
