T* (              "title": "The big idea",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "**Position** \($x$\) is an object's location measured from a chosen reference point \(the ) Tj
T* (origin\) along a chosen axis. Position needs a sign: $+x$ to one side of the origin, $-x$ to the ) Tj
T* (other.\\n\\n**Displacement** \($\\\\Delta x$\) is the *change* in position -- how far and in which direction the object ended ) Tj
T* (up relative to where it started:\\n\\n$$\\\\Delta x = x_f - x_i$$\\n\\nDisplacement is a **vector**: it has both size and ) Tj
T* (direction \(a sign\). \\n\\n**Distance** is the total length of the path actually travelled. Distance is a **scalar**: it ) Tj
T* (has size only, is never negative, and ignores direction.\\n\\nThe key consequence:\\n\\n- If you walk $5\\\\,\\\\text{m}$ east, ) Tj
T* (then $2\\\\,\\\\text{m}$ west, your **distance** is $7\\\\,\\\\text{m}$ but your **displacement** is $+3\\\\,\\\\text{m}$ \(east\).\\n-) Tj
T* ( Distance is always **greater than or equal to** the magnitude of displacement: $\\\\text{distance} \\\\ge |\\\\Delta x|$. ) Tj
T* (They are equal only when motion never reverses direction.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "WORKED_EXAMPLES",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Worked examples",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "examples": [) Tj
T* (                  {) Tj
T* (                    "title": "There and partway back",) Tj
T* (                    "problem": "Maya starts at $x_i = 0$, walks to $x = +5\\\\,\\\\text{m}$, then back to $x_f = ) Tj
T* (+3\\\\,\\\\text{m}$. Find her displacement and the distance she walked.",) Tj
T* (                    "steps": [) Tj
T* (                      "Displacement uses only start and end: $\\\\Delta x = x_f - x_i = 3 - 0 = +3\\\\,\\\\text{m}$.",) Tj
ET
endstream
