T* (                "markdown": "On a line, direction is just a sign. In two or three dimensions, displacement becomes a ) Tj
T* (true vector $\\\\vec{\\\\Delta r} = \\\\langle \\\\Delta x, \\\\Delta y, \\\\Delta z\\\\rangle$, and its magnitude comes from the ) Tj
T* (Pythagorean theorem: $|\\\\vec{\\\\Delta r}| = \\\\sqrt{\\\\Delta x^2 + \\\\Delta y^2}$. Distance is still the length of the ) Tj
T* (actual \(possibly curved\) path -- found with calculus as the integral of speed over time. We'll meet that idea again.") Tj
