T* (velocity at a single instant -- what a speedometer \(plus a direction\) reads. It is the limit of average velocity over a ) Tj
T* (vanishingly small time interval, i.e. the derivative of position with respect to time:\\n\\n$$v = \\\\lim_{\\\\Delta t \\\\to ) Tj
T* (0}\\\\frac{\\\\Delta x}{\\\\Delta t} = \\\\frac{dx}{dt}$$\\n\\nThat calculus definition is the bridge between this algebra-based ) Tj
T* (course and the full university treatment. **Instantaneous speed** is just the magnitude $|v|$.\\n\\n**Unit conversion** ) Tj
