T* (              "title": "Deeper dive: inertial reference frames",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "The first law actually *defines* a special class of viewpoints called **inertial reference ) Tj
T* (frames** -- frames that are not accelerating. In an accelerating frame \(a braking bus\), objects seem to violate the ) Tj
T* (first law \(you lurch forward with no obvious force\), which is why we invent \\"fictitious\\" forces to describe them. ) Tj
T* (Einstein took this puzzle about frames and inertia and built it into general relativity.") Tj
