T* (                "scene": "sun",) Tj
T* (                "headline": "Force = Mass x Acceleration",) Tj
T* (                "sub": "The most useful equation in mechanics ties together the push, the stuff being pushed, and how ) Tj
T* (its motion changes.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONTEXT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Why this matters",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Newton's second law is the workhorse of classical physics. It predicts how rockets launch, ) Tj
T* (how cars stop, how planets orbit, and how a tossed ball arcs. Give it the net force and the mass, and it hands you the ) Tj
T* (acceleration -- and from kinematics, the entire future of the motion.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONCEPT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "The big idea",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "**Newton's Second Law:** the acceleration of an object is proportional to the net force on ) Tj
T* (it and inversely proportional to its mass:\\n\\n$$\\\\vec F_{net} = m\\\\,\\\\vec a \\\\qquad\\\\Longleftrightarrow\\\\qquad \\\\vec a =) Tj
T* ( \\\\frac{\\\\vec F_{net}}{m}$$\\n\\nThree readings of the same law:\\n\\n- **Bigger force => bigger acceleration** \(same ) Tj
T* (mass\).\\n- **Bigger mass => smaller acceleration** \(same force\).\\n- Acceleration points in the **same direction** as the ) Tj
T* (net force.\\n\\nThe SI unit of force is the **newton**: $1\\\\ \\\\text{N} = 1\\\\ \\\\text{kg}\\\\cdot\\\\text{m/s}^2$ -- exactly the) Tj
T* ( force that accelerates $1\\\\,\\\\text{kg}$ at $1\\\\,\\\\text{m/s}^2$.\\n\\nBecause force is a vector, you usually start with a ) Tj
T* (**free-body diagram**: draw every force acting on the object as an arrow, then add them as vectors to get $\\\\vec ) Tj
T* (F_{net}$. The first law is just the special case $\\\\vec a = 0$ when $\\\\vec F_{net} = 0$.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
ET
endstream
