T* (              "kind": "DEEPER_DIVE",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Deeper dive: the law is really about momentum",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Newton actually wrote the second law in terms of **momentum** $\\\\vec p = m\\\\vec v$: the net) Tj
T* ( force equals the rate of change of momentum,\\n\\n$$\\\\vec F_{net} = \\\\frac{d\\\\vec p}{dt}.$$\\n\\nWhen mass is constant this) Tj
T* ( becomes $\\\\vec F = m\\\\dfrac{d\\\\vec v}{dt} = m\\\\vec a$ -- our familiar form. But the momentum version is more general: ) Tj
T* (it correctly handles systems whose **mass changes**, like a rocket burning fuel, and it survives into relativity where ) Tj
T* ($m\\\\vec a$ does not.") Tj
