T* (                "headline": "Equal and Opposite",) Tj
T* (                "sub": "You cannot touch without being touched back. Every force is one half of a pair.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONTEXT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Why this matters",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Rockets work in the vacuum of space with nothing to push against -- except the exhaust they) Tj
T* ( throw out. Walking, swimming, flying, and recoil are all the third law in action. Understanding it correctly clears up ) Tj
T* (one of the most common misconceptions in all of physics.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONCEPT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "The big idea",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "**Newton's Third Law:** for every force \(an *action*\), there is an equal and opposite force) Tj
T* ( \(a *reaction*\):\\n\\n$$\\\\vec F_{A \\\\to B} = -\\\\,\\\\vec F_{B \\\\to A}$$\\n\\nIf object A pushes on object B, then B pushes ) Tj
T* (back on A with **equal magnitude** and **opposite direction**.\\n\\nThe key subtlety -- and the source of endless ) Tj
T* (confusion: **the two forces act on different objects.** Because they act on *different* bodies, they do **not** cancel ) Tj
T* (each other out. \(Only forces on the *same* object can cancel.\)\\n\\nExamples:\\n\\n- You push the ground backward with your ) Tj
T* (foot; the ground pushes you forward -- that's how you walk.\\n- A rocket pushes exhaust gases down/back; the gases push ) Tj
T* (the rocket up/forward.\\n- A swimmer pushes water backward; the water pushes the swimmer forward.\\n- Fire a gun: it ) Tj
T* (pushes the bullet forward, the bullet pushes the gun back \(recoil\).") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "WORKED_EXAMPLES",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Worked examples",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "examples": [) Tj
T* (                  {) Tj
T* (                    "title": "Pushing a wall",) Tj
T* (                    "problem": "You push on a wall with $50\\\\,\\\\text{N}$. How hard does the wall push on you?",) Tj
ET
endstream
