T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "A classic puzzle: \\"If the cart pulls back on the horse just as hard as the horse pulls the) Tj
T* ( cart, how can they ever move?\\" The resolution: those two forces act on **different objects** \(one on the cart, one on ) Tj
T* (the horse\), so they don't cancel. To see if the *cart* accelerates, add up only the forces on the cart: the horse's ) Tj
T* (forward pull versus the cart's friction. The horse, meanwhile, accelerates because the **ground** pushes its hooves ) Tj
T* (forward harder than the cart pulls it back. Same law, careful bookkeeping.") Tj
