T* (              "title": "Practice problems",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "intro": "Use $f = \\\\mu N$, and remember static friction only rises to its maximum.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "DEEPER_DIVE",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Deeper dive: why friction barely depends on area",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "It seems strange that a brick slides with the same friction lying flat or on its end, ) Tj
T* (despite very different contact areas. The reason: real surfaces touch only at tiny high spots \(\\"asperities\\"\). ) Tj
T* (Spreading the same weight over a larger area lowers the pressure but increases the number of contact points -- the two ) Tj
T* (effects roughly cancel, so total friction depends on the **normal force**, not the apparent area. This is captured in ) Tj
T* (the simple law $f = \\\\mu N$, an empirical approximation that works remarkably well.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "SUMMARY",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Summary",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "takeaways": [) Tj
T* (                  "Friction opposes sliding and acts parallel to the surface.",) Tj
T* (                  "Static: $f_s \\\\le \\\\mu_s N$ \(adjusts up to a max\). Kinetic: $f_k = \\\\mu_k N$.",) Tj
T* (                  "$N$ is the normal force; usually $\\\\mu_s > \\\\mu_k$.",) Tj
T* (                  "Friction depends on normal force \(not area or speed\) and makes heat.") Tj
T* (                ],) Tj
T* (                "formulas": [) Tj
T* (                  {) Tj
T* (                    "label": "Static friction",) Tj
T* (                    "tex": "f_s \\\\le \\\\mu_s N") Tj
T* (                  },) Tj
T* (                  {) Tj
T* (                    "label": "Kinetic friction",) Tj
T* (                    "tex": "f_k = \\\\mu_k N") Tj
T* (                  }) Tj
T* (                ]) Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            }) Tj
T* (          ],) Tj
