T* (                "headline": "Doing Work",) Tj
T* (                "sub": "In physics, work has a precise meaning: a force only does work when it moves something along its) Tj
T* ( own direction.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONTEXT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Why this matters",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "\\"Work\\" in physics is not effort or tiredness -- holding a heavy box perfectly still is ) Tj
T* (exhausting but does **zero** work, because nothing moves. Defining work precisely is the gateway to the single most ) Tj
T* (powerful idea in physics: **energy**. Work is exactly the mechanism by which energy is transferred from one object to ) Tj
T* (another.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
