T* (              "kind": "CONCEPT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "The big idea",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "**Work** is done when a force acts on an object and moves it through a displacement. For a ) Tj
T* (constant force,\\n\\n$$W = F\\\\,d\\\\cos\\\\theta$$\\n\\nwhere $F$ is the force magnitude, $d$ is the displacement, and $\\\\theta$) Tj
T* ( is the angle between the force and the displacement.\\n\\n- If the force is **along** the motion \($\\\\theta = 0$\): $W = ) Tj
T* (Fd$ \(maximum, positive work\).\\n- If the force is **perpendicular** to the motion \($\\\\theta = 90^\\\\circ$\): $\\\\cos ) Tj
T* (90^\\\\circ = 0$, so $W = 0$. \(Carrying a box horizontally does no work *against gravity* -- gravity points down, motion ) Tj
T* (is sideways.\)\\n- If the force **opposes** the motion \($\\\\theta = 180^\\\\circ$\): $W = -Fd$ \(negative work, like friction ) Tj
T* (removing energy\).\\n\\nThe SI unit of work is the **joule**: $1\\\\ \\\\text{J} = 1\\\\ \\\\text{N}\\\\cdot\\\\text{m}$. Work is a ) Tj
T* (**scalar** -- it has no direction, only a sign.\\n\\nThe deep meaning: **work is energy transferred.** Positive work adds ) Tj
T* (energy to an object; negative work takes it away.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
