T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Potential energy and force are two sides of the same coin. The force is the **negative ) Tj
T* (slope** of the potential energy curve:\\n\\n$$F = -\\\\frac{dU}{dx}.$$\\n\\nFor a spring, $U = \\\\tfrac12 kx^2$, and its slope ) Tj
T* (is $kx$, giving the restoring force $F = -kx$ -- Hooke's law falls right out. Objects always tend to roll \\"downhill\\" ) Tj
T* (on a potential-energy graph, toward lower energy. This picture of energy *landscapes* runs all the way up to chemistry ) Tj
T* (and quantum mechanics.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
