T* (              "kind": "DEEPER_DIVE",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Deeper dive: why energy is conserved at all",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Energy conservation isn't just a handy rule -- it reflects something profound. A theorem by) Tj
T* ( Emmy Noether shows that **every conservation law comes from a symmetry of nature**. Conservation of energy follows from) Tj
T* ( the fact that the laws of physics are the **same at every moment in time** \(time-translation symmetry\). Conservation of) Tj
T* ( momentum comes from symmetry in space, and angular momentum from symmetry under rotation. This link between symmetry ) Tj
T* (and conservation is one of the most beautiful ideas in modern physics.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "SUMMARY",) Tj
