T* (                "takeaways": [) Tj
T* (                  "Total mechanical energy $E = K + U$.",) Tj
T* (                  "Without friction, $K_i + U_i = K_f + U_f$ -- energy is conserved.",) Tj
T* (                  "Energy converts between kinetic and potential, never vanishing.",) Tj
T* (                  "Falling from height $h$: $v = \\\\sqrt{2gh}$ \(mass cancels\).",) Tj
T* (                  "Friction converts mechanical energy to heat, but total energy is always conserved.") Tj
T* (                ],) Tj
T* (                "formulas": [) Tj
T* (                  {) Tj
T* (                    "label": "Conservation",) Tj
T* (                    "tex": "K_i + U_i = K_f + U_f") Tj
