T* (              "kind": "CONCEPT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "The big idea",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "**Power** is the **rate** at which work is done -- energy transferred per unit time:\\n\\n$$P) Tj
T* ( = \\\\frac{W}{t} = \\\\frac{\\\\Delta E}{t}.$$\\n\\nThe SI unit is the **watt**: $1\\\\ \\\\text{W} = 1\\\\ \\\\text{J/s}$. A 60-watt ) Tj
T* (bulb converts 60 joules of electrical energy every second.\\n\\nThere's a second, very useful form. Since $W = Fd$, ) Tj
T* (dividing by time gives $P = F\\\\dfrac{d}{t} = Fv$ -- power equals force times speed:\\n\\n$$P = F v.$$\\n\\nThis is why a car) Tj
T* ( needs far more engine power to maintain high speed \(the drag force is large *and* you're moving fast\), and why climbing) Tj
T* ( stairs quickly takes more power than climbing them slowly, even though the work \(your weight times the height\) is ) Tj
T* (identical.\\n\\nA handy energy unit comes from power: the **kilowatt-hour** is the energy of one kilowatt running for one ) Tj
T* (hour -- that's what your utility actually charges for.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
