T* (                "headline": "Mass in Motion",) Tj
T* (                "sub": "A slow truck and a fast bullet can be equally hard to stop. Momentum captures the 'quantity of ) Tj
T* (motion', and impulse is how you change it.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONTEXT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Why this matters",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Why do airbags, crumple zones, and follow-through in sports all work? They all manage ) Tj
T* (**impulse** -- stretching out the time over which momentum changes to soften the force. Momentum is also the conserved ) Tj
T* (quantity that lets us analyse collisions and rocket flight where energy methods alone fall short.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONCEPT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "The big idea",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "**Momentum** is mass times velocity:\\n\\n$$\\\\vec p = m\\\\vec v.$$\\n\\nIt's a **vector** \(it ) Tj
T* (has direction\), measured in $\\\\text{kg*m/s}$. A heavy slow object and a light fast one can carry the same ) Tj
T* (momentum.\\n\\n**Impulse** is what changes momentum. From Newton's second law in its original form, $\\\\vec F = ) Tj
T* (\\\\dfrac{d\\\\vec p}{dt}$, a force acting over a time interval delivers an **impulse**:\\n\\n$$\\\\vec J = \\\\vec F\\\\,\\\\Delta t ) Tj
T* (= \\\\Delta \\\\vec p.$$\\n\\nThis is the **impulse-momentum theorem**: the impulse on an object equals its change in ) Tj
T* (momentum. Impulse is measured in $\\\\text{N*s}$, which is the same as $\\\\text{kg*m/s}$.\\n\\nThe practical punchline: to ) Tj
T* (produce a given change in momentum \(say, stopping a moving car\), a **longer** contact time means a **smaller** force. An) Tj
T* ( airbag increases $\\\\Delta t$, so the force on you, $F = \\\\Delta p / \\\\Delta t$, drops. Same $\\\\Delta p$, gentler ride.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "WORKED_EXAMPLES",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Worked examples",) Tj
