T* (              "kind": "DEEPER_DIVE",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Deeper dive: why momentum, not just energy?",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Both energy and momentum are conserved, so why have two? Because they capture **different**) Tj
T* ( things. Momentum is a **vector** and is conserved in *every* collision, even when kinetic energy is lost to heat. ) Tj
T* (Kinetic energy is a **scalar** and is only conserved in *elastic* collisions. Having both lets you solve for two ) Tj
T* (unknowns \(two final velocities\) in an elastic collision. Momentum also handles direction -- head-on versus glancing -- ) Tj
T* (which energy alone can't. The two laws are partners, not rivals.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
