T* (              "kind": "CONCEPT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "The big idea",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "**Conservation of momentum:** if no net *external* force acts on a system, its **total ) Tj
T* (momentum stays constant**:\\n\\n$$\\\\vec p_{i,\\\\text{total}} = \\\\vec p_{f,\\\\text{total}}.$$\\n\\nFor two objects interacting ) Tj
T* (\(a collision, an explosion, a push-off\):\\n\\n$$m_1 \\\\vec v_{1i} + m_2 \\\\vec v_{2i} = m_1 \\\\vec v_{1f} + m_2 \\\\vec ) Tj
T* (v_{2f}.$$\\n\\nWhy is it true? During the interaction, object 1 pushes on object 2 and \(Newton's third law\) object 2 ) Tj
T* (pushes back equally and oppositely. These internal forces give equal-and-opposite impulses, so whatever momentum one ) Tj
T* (object gains, the other loses. The **total** can't change.\\n\\nConsequences you can see everywhere:\\n\\n- **Recoil.** Fire) Tj
T* ( a bullet forward and the gun must move backward so the total stays the same \(it started at zero\).\\n- **Push-off.** Two ) Tj
T* (skaters at rest shove apart; they fly in opposite directions with equal and opposite momenta.\\n- **Sticking together.** ) Tj
T* (Two carts that couple move off with the combined momentum they had before.\\n\\nMomentum is a vector, so **directions ) Tj
T* (matter** -- choose a positive direction and give opposing velocities opposite signs.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
