T* (This leads to the **Tsiolkovsky rocket equation**, $\\\\Delta v = v_e \\\\ln\\\\dfrac{m_0}{m_f}$, which says your change in ) Tj
T* (speed depends on the exhaust speed $v_e$ and the *ratio* of starting to ending mass. It's why rockets are mostly fuel --) Tj
T* ( and why getting to orbit is so hard.") Tj
