(              "kind": "CONCEPT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "The big idea",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "In a **perfectly inelastic collision**, the objects **stick together** and move as one ) Tj
T* (afterward. Momentum conservation gives their common final velocity directly:\\n\\n$$m_1 v_1 + m_2 v_2 = \(m_1 + m_2\)\\\\,v_f ) Tj
T* (\\\\;\\\\Rightarrow\\\\; v_f = \\\\frac{m_1 v_1 + m_2 v_2}{m_1 + m_2}.$$\\n\\nThe defining feature: **kinetic energy is *not* ) Tj
T* (conserved.** Some of it is converted into heat, sound, and permanent deformation as the objects crush and stick. ) Tj
T* (Momentum is *always* conserved \(no external force\), but kinetic energy drops:\\n\\n$$K_f < K_i.$$\\n\\nThe \\"lost\\" kinetic ) Tj
T* (energy hasn't vanished -- by conservation of *total* energy it became heat and deformation. \(A collision in which the ) Tj
T* (objects don't stick but still lose some kinetic energy is just *inelastic*; the maximum possible energy loss happens ) Tj
T* (when they stick -- *perfectly* inelastic.\)") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "SIMULATION",) Tj
