T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "The **center of mass** \(CM\) is the **mass-weighted average position** of all the parts of a) Tj
T* ( system. For two objects on a line:\\n\\n$$x_{cm} = \\\\frac{m_1 x_1 + m_2 x_2}{m_1 + m_2}.$$\\n\\n\(For many objects, sum $m_i) Tj
T* ( x_i$ over all of them and divide by the total mass.\)\\n\\nKey properties:\\n\\n- The CM lies **closer to the heavier** ) Tj
T* (object. For equal masses it sits exactly **halfway** between them.\\n- The whole system **moves as if all its mass were ) Tj
