T* (              "kind": "DEEPER_DIVE",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Deeper dive: torque as a cross product",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Fully, torque is a **vector**: $\\\\vec\\\\tau = \\\\vec r \\\\times \\\\vec F$, the cross product of) Tj
T* ( the position and force vectors. Its magnitude is $rF\\\\sin\\\\theta$ \(our formula\) and its **direction** is along the ) Tj
T* (rotation axis, given by the right-hand rule. This is why torque, like angular velocity and angular momentum, points ) Tj
T* (along the axis of spin rather than in the plane of motion. The cross-product structure is what makes gyroscopes precess ) Tj
T* (in their strange, counter-intuitive way.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
