T* (              "kind": "DEEPER_DIVE",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Deeper dive: the parallel-axis theorem",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Moment of inertia depends on *which axis* you spin about. The **parallel-axis theorem** ) Tj
T* (gives a shortcut: if you know $I_{cm}$ about an axis through the center of mass, then about any parallel axis a distance) Tj
T* ( $d$ away,\\n\\n$$I = I_{cm} + Md^2.$$\\n\\nThis is why a rod is much harder to spin about its end than about its middle -- ) Tj
T* (you've added $Md^2$. It also explains why holding a heavy object far from your body strains you: you've increased the ) Tj
T* (effective moment of inertia your muscles must control.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
