T* (          "tagline": "The spin that's hard to stop",) Tj
T* (          "estMinutes": 15,) Tj
T* (          "xpReward": 180,) Tj
T* (          "sections": [) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "HERO",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "scene": "sun",) Tj
T* (                "headline": "Conserved Spin",) Tj
T* (                "sub": "Pull your arms in and you spin faster. Angular momentum is conserved -- the rotational twin of ) Tj
T* (momentum.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONTEXT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Why this matters",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "A figure skater's spin-up, a gyroscope's stubborn axis, a collapsing star becoming a ) Tj
T* (millisecond pulsar -- all are conservation of angular momentum. It's one of the great conservation laws, and it governs ) Tj
T* (everything that turns, from atoms to galaxies.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONCEPT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "The big idea",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "**Angular momentum** is the rotational version of momentum:\\n\\n$$L = I\\\\omega.$$\\n\\nIt's ) Tj
T* (measured in $\\\\text{kg*m}^2/\\\\text{s}$. Just as a net force changes momentum, a **net torque** changes angular momentum:) Tj
T* ( $\\\\tau_{net} = \\\\dfrac{dL}{dt}$.\\n\\n**Conservation of angular momentum:** with **no net external torque**, total ) Tj
T* (angular momentum stays constant:\\n\\n$$I_i \\\\omega_i = I_f \\\\omega_f.$$\\n\\nHere's the magic: an object can change its ) Tj
T* (**own** moment of inertia by redistributing its mass, and $\\\\omega$ must adjust to keep $L$ fixed. Pull mass *inward* ) Tj
T* (and $I$ drops, so $\\\\omega$ must rise -- you spin **faster**.\\n\\n- A **figure skater** pulls their arms in, shrinking ) Tj
T* ($I$, and spins up dramatically.\\n- A **collapsing star** shrinks enormously, so its spin rate skyrockets -- forming a ) Tj
T* (pulsar rotating hundreds of times per second.\\n- A **diver** tucks to spin fast, then opens up to slow the rotation for ) Tj
T* (a clean entry.\\n\\nAngular momentum is also a **vector** along the spin axis, which is why a spinning top or gyroscope ) Tj
T* (resists tipping -- changing its direction would require a torque.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "SIMULATION",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Try it: balance and torque",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "simId": "torque-balance",) Tj
T* (                "intro": "Revisit torque on the balance beam -- recall that it's a net torque that changes angular ) Tj
T* (momentum. With zero net torque, spin \(angular momentum\) stays constant.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "WORKED_EXAMPLES",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Worked examples",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
