T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Like energy and linear momentum, conservation of angular momentum springs from a ) Tj
T* (**symmetry** \(Noether's theorem\): the laws of physics are the same in every **direction** -- *rotational symmetry* of ) Tj
T* (space. Because nature has no preferred orientation, angular momentum is conserved. This is why it holds everywhere, from) Tj
T* ( the electron's quantised spin to the rotation of entire galaxies, and why a gyroscope can keep a spacecraft pointed at ) Tj
T* (a distant star for years.") Tj
