T* (              "title": "Deeper dive: why the acceleration points inward",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Over a tiny time $\\\\Delta t$ the velocity vector turns by a small angle but keeps the same ) Tj
T* (length. The **change** in velocity, $\\\\Delta \\\\vec v = \\\\vec v_f - \\\\vec v_i$, points toward the center of the circle --) Tj
T* ( and $\\\\vec a = \\\\Delta \\\\vec v / \\\\Delta t$ inherits that direction. Taking the limit $\\\\Delta t \\\\to 0$ gives a vector) Tj
T* ( that always points exactly at the center, with magnitude $v^2/r$. This is the geometric origin of centripetal ) Tj
T* (acceleration, and the same limiting argument is the derivative in disguise.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
