T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONTEXT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Two stars, one rhythm",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Binary stars trace each other in a steady, repeating dance -- the same periodic rhythm as a) Tj
T* ( mass bouncing on a spring or a child on a swing. When the force pulling a system back to equilibrium grows in ) Tj
T* (proportion to how far it's displaced, you get **simple harmonic motion \(SHM\)**, the template for all oscillation.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONCEPT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "The big idea",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "**Simple harmonic motion** occurs when the restoring force is proportional to displacement ) Tj
T* (and points back toward equilibrium -- **Hooke's law**:\\n\\n$$F = -kx,$$\\n\\nwhere $k$ is the stiffness and the minus sign ) Tj
T* (means 'always back toward center'.\\n\\nThe motion in time is a sinusoid:\\n\\n$$x\(t\) = A\\\\cos\(\\\\omega t\),$$\\n\\nwith ) Tj
T* (**amplitude** $A$ \(the maximum displacement\) and **angular frequency** $\\\\omega$. For a mass $m$ on a ) Tj
T* (spring,\\n\\n$$\\\\omega = \\\\sqrt{\\\\frac{k}{m}}, \\\\qquad T = 2\\\\pi\\\\sqrt{\\\\frac{m}{k}}.$$\\n\\nThe **period** $T$ is the time ) Tj
T* (for one full cycle; **frequency** $f = 1/T$ is cycles per second \(hertz\). Notice the period does **not** depend on ) Tj
T* (amplitude -- a wider swing simply moves faster, taking the same time. Energy sloshes between elastic potential ) Tj
T* (\($\\\\tfrac12 kx^2$\) and kinetic \($\\\\tfrac12 mv^2$\), summing to a constant.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
