T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONTEXT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "From spark to circuit",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Static charge is dramatic but fleeting. Channel charge into a steady **flow** through wires) Tj
T* ( and you get a **circuit** -- the basis of every device you own. Three quantities -- voltage, current, resistance -- and) Tj
T* ( one law connect them.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONCEPT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "The big idea",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Three quantities describe a simple circuit:\\n\\n- **Voltage** $V$ \(volts\): the energy per ) Tj
T* (charge driving the flow -- the 'push'.\\n- **Current** $I$ \(amperes\): the rate of charge flow -- how much passes per ) Tj
T* (second.\\n- **Resistance** $R$ \(ohms\): how strongly the path opposes the flow.\\n\\n**Ohm's law** links them:\\n\\n$$V = ) Tj
T* (I\\\\,R.$$\\n\\nSo $I = \\\\dfrac{V}{R}$ -- more voltage drives more current; more resistance chokes it. The water analogy: ) Tj
T* (voltage is the pump pressure, current is the flow rate, resistance is a narrow pipe.\\n\\n**Electrical power** delivered ) Tj
T* (is\\n\\n$$P = VI = I^2R,$$\\n\\nin watts -- the rate energy is converted to light, heat, or motion.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
