T* ( fight through. In **parallel** \(side by side\) they combine as $\\\\dfrac1R = \\\\dfrac1{R_1} + \\\\dfrac1{R_2}$, giving ) Tj
T* (*less* total resistance because the current has more paths. These two rules, plus Ohm's law, let you analyse any network) Tj
T* ( -- and they're the electrical cousins of how springs combine and how pipes share flow.") Tj
