T* (                "headline": "The Speed Limit of the Universe",) Tj
T* (                "sub": "Hold the speed of light constant for everyone, and space and time themselves must bend to ) Tj
T* (comply.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONTEXT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "When stars explode",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "A supernova flings matter outward at a sizeable fraction of light speed, and converts mass ) Tj
T* (into staggering energy. To describe such speeds, Newton's mechanics fails and Einstein's **special relativity** takes ) Tj
T* (over -- built on two deceptively simple postulates with shocking consequences.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONCEPT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "The big idea",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Special relativity rests on two postulates:\\n\\n1. The laws of physics are the same in every) Tj
T* ( inertial \(non-accelerating\) frame.\\n2. The speed of light $c \\\\approx 3\\\\times10^8\\\\,\\\\text{m/s}$ is the same for ) Tj
T* (**all** observers, regardless of their motion.\\n\\nThe second is the radical one. To keep $c$ constant, space and time ) Tj
T* (must adjust:\\n\\n- **Time dilation:** a moving clock runs slow, by the factor $\\\\gamma = \\\\dfrac{1}{\\\\sqrt{1 - ) Tj
T* (v^2/c^2}}$.\\n- **Length contraction:** a moving object is shortened along its motion.\\n- Nothing with mass can reach $c$) Tj
T* ( -- $\\\\gamma$ blows up as $v \\\\to c$.\\n\\nAnd mass itself is a form of energy, the most famous equation in ) Tj
T* (physics:\\n\\n$$E = mc^2.$$\\n\\nA tiny mass holds enormous energy because $c^2$ is huge -- the engine of stars and ) Tj
T* (supernovae alike.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "WORKED_EXAMPLES",) Tj
