T* (              "kind": "CONTEXT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "What holds a neutron star up",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "A neutron star is heavier than the Sun, squeezed into a city. What stops it collapsing ) Tj
T* (further isn't heat -- it's a purely **quantum** effect: degeneracy pressure, born from the wave nature of matter and the) Tj
T* ( rule that identical particles can't share a state. To understand it, we start with the strangest idea in physics: ) Tj
T* (matter is made of waves.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONCEPT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "The big idea",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "**Wave-particle duality:** every particle has a wavelength, given by **de ) Tj
T* (Broglie**:\\n\\n$$\\\\lambda = \\\\frac{h}{p},$$\\n\\nwhere $p = mv$ is momentum and $h$ is Planck's constant. Big objects have ) Tj
T* (absurdly tiny wavelengths \(hence we never notice\), but electrons' wavelengths are atom-sized -- and they diffract like ) Tj
T* (waves.\\n\\nA quantum system is described by a **wavefunction** $\\\\psi\(x\)$. Born's rule: $|\\\\psi\(x\)|^2$ is the ) Tj
T* (**probability density** of finding the particle at $x$. Quantum mechanics predicts **probabilities**, not ) Tj
T* (certainties.\\n\\nConsequences:\\n\\n- The **double-slit experiment**: single electrons build up an interference pattern -- ) Tj
T* (each one passes through 'both slits' as a wave.\\n- **Heisenberg uncertainty:** $\\\\Delta x\\\\,\\\\Delta p \\\\gtrsim ) Tj
T* (\\\\dfrac{\\\\hbar}{2}$ -- position and momentum can't both be sharp.\\n\\nThis is not ignorance; it's how nature is built at ) Tj
T* (the smallest scales.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "WORKED_EXAMPLES",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Worked examples",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "examples": [) Tj
T* (                  {) Tj
T* (                    "title": "de Broglie",) Tj
T* (                    "problem": "How does wavelength depend on momentum?",) Tj
