T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "A quantum particle is described by a **wavefunction** $\\\\psi\(x\)$. The wavefunction itself ) Tj
T* (isn't directly observable, but its square gives the **probability** of finding the particle at each location:\\n\\n$$P\(x\) ) Tj
T* (\\\\propto |\\\\psi\(x\)|^2.$$\\n\\nKey consequences:\\n\\n- Before measurement, the particle is in a **superposition** -- a blend) Tj
T* ( of possible positions \(and states\). It has no single value.\\n- **Measurement** forces a definite outcome at random, ) Tj
T* (weighted by $|\\\\psi|^2$ -- the wavefunction 'collapses.'\\n- Total probability must equal 1: the particle is ) Tj
T* (*somewhere*.\\n- The shape of $\\\\psi$ over time follows the **Schr?dinger equation**, the quantum law of motion.\\n\\nThis ) Tj
T* (is why quantum mechanics is **probabilistic**: it predicts the odds of outcomes, not certainties. Einstein resisted it ) Tj
T* (-- 'God does not play dice' -- but experiment has sided with the dice every time.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
