T* (                "headline": "Held Up by a Rule, Not a Fire",) Tj
T* (                "sub": "A neutron star resists collapse not with heat or fuel, but with a quantum law about how ) Tj
T* (particles may be packed.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONTEXT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "What holds a neutron star up?",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "A neutron star has burned out -- no fusion fights gravity. Yet it doesn't collapse to a ) Tj
T* (point. The reason is purely quantum: **degeneracy pressure**, a consequence of the **Pauli exclusion principle**. And ) Tj
T* (the same quantum strangeness lets the Sun fuse at all, through **tunnelling**.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONCEPT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "The big idea",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Two deeply quantum effects:\\n\\n**Quantum tunnelling.** Because a particle is a spread-out ) Tj
T* (wave, it has a small probability of being found *beyond* an energy barrier it classically could never cross. It can ) Tj
T* ('tunnel' through. This is how protons in the Sun fuse despite their electric repulsion -- classically they'd never get ) Tj
T* (close enough; quantum-mechanically a few tunnel through and ignite the star. Tunnelling also drives radioactive alpha ) Tj
T* (decay and the transistors in your phone.\\n\\n**The Pauli exclusion principle & degeneracy pressure.** Identical fermions ) Tj
T* (\(electrons, neutrons\) cannot occupy the same quantum state. Crush matter and the particles are forced into ) Tj
T* (ever-higher-energy states -- they resist being packed, producing **degeneracy pressure** that needs no heat. This ) Tj
T* (pressure holds up **white dwarfs** \(electron degeneracy\) and **neutron stars** \(neutron degeneracy\). Exceed the limit ) Tj
T* (\(about 1.4 solar masses for a white dwarf -- the **Chandrasekhar limit**\) and even this fails: the star collapses to a ) Tj
T* (neutron star or a black hole.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
