(              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Newton's gravity is astonishingly accurate, but it has a puzzle: how does the Sun reach ) Tj
T* (across empty space to pull the Earth, instantly? Einstein's **general relativity** dissolves the puzzle by reimagining ) Tj
T* (gravity entirely -- not as a force, but as the **curvature of spacetime**, the stage on which black holes are written.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONCEPT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "The big idea",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "General relativity rests on the **equivalence principle**: being in a gravitational field ) Tj
T* (is locally indistinguishable from accelerating. Standing on Earth feels exactly like riding an accelerating rocket -- so) Tj
T* ( gravity and acceleration are the same thing.\\n\\nFrom this, Einstein concluded that **mass and energy curve spacetime**,) Tj
T* ( and objects in free fall simply follow the straightest possible paths \(**geodesics**\) through that curved geometry. ) Tj
T* (Summarized by Wheeler:\\n\\n> *Spacetime tells matter how to move; matter tells spacetime how to curve.*\\n\\nPredictions, ) Tj
T* (all confirmed:\\n\\n- **Light bends** near mass \(gravitational lensing\).\\n- **Time runs slower** in stronger gravity ) Tj
T* (\(gravitational time dilation -- your GPS corrects for it\).\\n- **Orbits precess**, explaining Mercury's anomaly that ) Tj
T* (Newton couldn't.\\n\\nGravity, in this view, is not a force at all -- it's the geometry of the universe.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "WORKED_EXAMPLES",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Worked examples",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "examples": [) Tj
T* (                  {) Tj
T* (                    "title": "Equivalence",) Tj
T* (                    "problem": "How does standing on Earth relate to accelerating?",) Tj
T* (                    "steps": [) Tj
T* (                      "Both feel identical locally.",) Tj
T* (                      "Equivalence principle.") Tj
T* (                    ],) Tj
T* (                    "answer": "Gravity ~= acceleration.") Tj
T* (                  },) Tj
T* (                  {) Tj
T* (                    "title": "Light and gravity",) Tj
T* (                    "problem": "Does gravity affect light?",) Tj
T* (                    "steps": [) Tj
T* (                      "Light follows spacetime geodesics.",) Tj
T* (                      "Curved near mass.") Tj
T* (                    ],) Tj
T* (                    "answer": "Yes -- light bends \(lensing\).") Tj
T* (                  },) Tj
T* (                  {) Tj
T* (                    "title": "Time",) Tj
T* (                    "problem": "Where do clocks run slower?",) Tj
T* (                    "steps": [) Tj
T* (                      "Stronger gravity = more time dilation.",) Tj
T* (                      "Lower clocks tick slow.") Tj
T* (                    ],) Tj
T* (                    "answer": "Deeper in a gravity well.") Tj
T* (                  }) Tj
T* (                ]) Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONCEPT_CHECK",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Quick check",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "intro": "Gravity = curved spacetime; equivalence principle.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "PRACTICE",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Practice problems",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "intro": "Reason about curvature, light, and time.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "DEEPER_DIVE",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Deeper dive: the Einstein field equations",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "All of this is captured in one compact line, the **Einstein field equations**: ) Tj
T* ($G_{\\\\mu\\\\nu} = \\\\dfrac{8\\\\pi G}{c^4} T_{\\\\mu\\\\nu}$. The left side \($G_{\\\\mu\\\\nu}$\) measures the curvature of spacetime;) Tj
T* ( the right side \($T_{\\\\mu\\\\nu}$\) measures the energy and momentum present. The equation says, precisely, that energy ) Tj
T* (curves geometry. Its solutions describe everything from the expanding universe to gravitational waves -- ripples in ) Tj
T* (spacetime detected by LIGO in 2015, exactly a century after Einstein predicted them.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "SUMMARY",) Tj
ET
