T* (              "title": "When gravity wins",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "When a massive star's core collapses and no pressure can stop it, spacetime curves so ) Tj
T* (steeply that a region forms from which **nothing escapes** -- a **black hole**. It is general relativity taken to its ) Tj
T* (logical extreme, and a real object we have now photographed.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONCEPT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "The big idea",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "**Escape velocity** is the speed needed to break free of a mass. Pack enough mass into a ) Tj
T* (small enough radius and the escape velocity reaches the speed of light $c$ -- beyond that boundary, nothing, not even ) Tj
T* (light, can escape. That is a **black hole**.\\n\\nThe boundary is the **event horizon**, at the **Schwarzschild ) Tj
T* (radius**:\\n\\n$$r_s = \\\\frac{2GM}{c^2}.$$\\n\\nIt is proportional to mass: double the mass, double the horizon. For the ) Tj
T* (Sun, $r_s \\\\approx 3\\\\,\\\\text{km}$; for Earth, about $9\\\\,\\\\text{mm}$.\\n\\n- Cross the horizon and all paths lead inward ) Tj
T* (to the **singularity** -- the future itself points down.\\n- The horizon isn't a surface of matter; it's a boundary in ) Tj
T* (spacetime.\\n- **Hawking radiation:** quantum effects let black holes slowly evaporate, the deepest known link between ) Tj
T* (gravity, quantum mechanics, and thermodynamics.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
