T* (          "tagline": "Einstein's happiest thought",) Tj
T* (          "estMinutes": 15,) Tj
T* (          "xpReward": 180,) Tj
T* (          "difficulty": 5,) Tj
T* (          "sections": [) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "HERO",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "scene": "sun",) Tj
T* (                "headline": "Falling Feels Like Floating",) Tj
T* (                "sub": "Einstein realized that a person in free fall feels no gravity at all -- the seed that grew into ) Tj
T* (a new theory of gravity.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONTEXT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "The thought behind the theory",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Before the curved spacetime of black holes comes the simple insight that made it possible. ) Tj
T* (Einstein called it his 'happiest thought': there is no experiment, done in a small sealed box, that can tell **gravity**) Tj
T* ( apart from **acceleration**. From that, all of general relativity unfolds.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONCEPT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "The big idea",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "The **equivalence principle**: locally, gravity and acceleration are ) Tj
T* (indistinguishable.\\n\\n- In a windowless lift accelerating upward in deep space at $9.8\\\\,\\\\text{m/s}^2$, you feel ) Tj
T* (pressed to the floor exactly as if standing on Earth.\\n- In a lift falling freely, you float -- gravity seems to vanish.) Tj
T* ( This is **weightlessness**: astronauts in orbit aren't beyond gravity, they're in continuous free fall.\\n\\nA deep clue ) Tj
T* (hides here: an object's **inertial mass** \(its resistance to acceleration, from $F = ma$\) exactly equals its ) Tj
T* (**gravitational mass** \(how strongly gravity pulls it\). Because they're equal, **all objects fall at the same rate** ) Tj
T* (regardless of mass -- Galileo's hammer and feather, confirmed on the airless Moon by Apollo 15.\\n\\nEinstein's leap: if ) Tj
T* (free fall erases gravity, then gravity isn't a force in the usual sense -- it's what motion looks like in **curved ) Tj
T* (spacetime**. Light, too, must bend in gravity, a prediction confirmed in 1919 by starlight deflected near the eclipsed ) Tj
T* (Sun, making Einstein world-famous overnight.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "WORKED_EXAMPLES",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Worked examples",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "examples": [) Tj
T* (                  {) Tj
T* (                    "title": "Lift vs. planet",) Tj
T* (                    "problem": "Can a sealed-box experiment tell gravity from acceleration?",) Tj
T* (                    "steps": [) Tj
T* (                      "Both press you to the floor identically.",) Tj
T* (                      "No local experiment distinguishes them.") Tj
T* (                    ],) Tj
T* (                    "answer": "No -- that is the equivalence principle.") Tj
T* (                  },) Tj
T* (                  {) Tj
T* (                    "title": "Why astronauts float",) Tj
T* (                    "problem": "Are orbiting astronauts beyond Earth's gravity?",) Tj
T* (                    "steps": [) Tj
T* (                      "Gravity is still strong in orbit.",) Tj
T* (                      "They are in continuous free fall.") Tj
T* (                    ],) Tj
T* (                    "answer": "No -- they float because they're freely falling.") Tj
T* (                  },) Tj
T* (                  {) Tj
T* (                    "title": "Equal fall rates",) Tj
T* (                    "problem": "Why do all objects fall at the same rate in a vacuum?",) Tj
T* (                    "steps": [) Tj
T* (                      "Inertial mass equals gravitational mass.",) Tj
T* (                      "The mass cancels in the motion.") Tj
T* (                    ],) Tj
T* (                    "answer": "Because the two kinds of mass are equal.") Tj
T* (                  }) Tj
ET
endstream
