T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONTEXT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "A galaxy of life stories",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "The Milky Way's hundreds of billions of stars are at every stage of life. By plotting them ) Tj
T* (on the **Hertzsprung-Russell diagram** -- luminosity versus temperature -- astronomers turned a scatter of points into ) Tj
T* (the biography of stars.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONCEPT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "The big idea",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "A star is a balance: **gravity** pulling in, **fusion pressure** pushing out. As long as it) Tj
T* ( fuses hydrogen in its core, it sits on the **main sequence** -- the diagonal band on the **HR diagram** where most ) Tj
T* (stars \(including the Sun\) spend ~90% of their lives.\\n\\nThe decisive factor is **mass**:\\n\\n- **Low-mass stars** \(like ) Tj
T* (the Sun\) swell into **red giants**, shed their outer layers, and leave a hot, dense **white dwarf** held up by electron ) Tj
T* (degeneracy.\\n- **High-mass stars** fuse heavier elements, then collapse and explode as a **supernova**, leaving a ) Tj
T* (**neutron star** or, if massive enough, a **black hole**.\\n\\nMore massive stars are hotter and vastly more luminous -- ) Tj
T* (but burn out far faster, living millions of years rather than billions. The heavy elements they forge and scatter become) Tj
T* ( the raw material for planets and life.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
