T* (              "kind": "DEEPER_DIVE",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Deeper dive: dating star clusters",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Stars in a cluster all formed together, so an HR diagram of a cluster is a snapshot of one ) Tj
T* (age. The most massive stars burn out first, peeling off the top of the main sequence. The point where the main sequence ) Tj
T* ('turns off' acts as a clock: the lower the turn-off, the older the cluster. This **main-sequence turn-off** method dates) Tj
T* ( the oldest globular clusters at over 12 billion years -- a check on the age of the universe itself.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
