(of an isolated system never decreases.\\n\\n$$\\\\Delta S_{\\\\text{total}} \\\\ge 0.$$\\n\\nConsequences:\\n\\n- Heat flows hot -> ) Tj
T* (cold because that spreads energy out, raising entropy.\\n- No engine can convert heat **entirely** into work -- some is ) Tj
