T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "HERO",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "scene": "sun",) Tj
T* (                "headline": "You Can't Win, and You Can't Break Even",) Tj
T* (                "sub": "Four deceptively simple laws rule every engine, star, and living cell -- and forbid the free ) Tj
T* (lunch forever.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONTEXT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "The rulebook of energy",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "The million-degree gas between galaxies, a car engine, your own metabolism -- all obey the ) Tj
T* (same handful of laws. Having met entropy and the second law, we now lay out the **full set**, the foundation of all ) Tj
T* (thermal physics.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONCEPT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "The big idea",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "The four laws of thermodynamics:\\n\\n**Zeroth law.** If two systems are each in thermal ) Tj
T* (equilibrium with a third, they're in equilibrium with each other. This is what makes **temperature** a meaningful, ) Tj
T* (measurable quantity -- it's why a thermometer works.\\n\\n**First law \(conservation of energy\).** Energy is conserved; you) Tj
T* ( can change a system's internal energy by adding **heat** $Q$ or doing **work** $W$ on it:\\n\\n$$\\\\Delta U = Q - ) Tj
T* (W.$$\\n\\nYou can't create energy from nothing -- *'you can't win.'*\\n\\n**Second law \(entropy\).** The total entropy of an ) Tj
T* (isolated system never decreases; heat flows spontaneously hot -> cold; no process is perfectly efficient -- *'you can't ) Tj
T* (break even.'* This law gives time its arrow.\\n\\n**Third law.** As temperature approaches **absolute zero**, entropy ) Tj
T* (approaches a minimum, and absolute zero itself can never be fully reached -- *'you can't get out of the ) Tj
T* (game.'*\\n\\nTogether they bound what any machine, chemical reaction, or living thing can do. They are among the most ) Tj
T* (universal laws in science -- Einstein expected them to be the one part of physics never overturned.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "WORKED_EXAMPLES",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Worked examples",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "examples": [) Tj
T* (                  {) Tj
T* (                    "title": "First law bookkeeping",) Tj
T* (                    "problem": "Heat $Q$ is added to a gas while it does work $W$. What is the change in internal ) Tj
T* (energy?",) Tj
T* (                    "steps": [) Tj
T* (                      "Energy is conserved.",) Tj
T* (                      "$\\\\Delta U = Q - W$.") Tj
T* (                    ],) Tj
T* (                    "answer": "$\\\\Delta U = Q - W$.") Tj
T* (                  },) Tj
T* (                  {) Tj
T* (                    "title": "Why thermometers work",) Tj
T* (                    "problem": "Which law guarantees temperature is well-defined?",) Tj
T* (                    "steps": [) Tj
T* (                      "Equilibrium is transitive.",) Tj
T* (                      "That's the zeroth law.") Tj
T* (                    ],) Tj
T* (                    "answer": "The zeroth law.") Tj
ET
endstream
endobj
