T* (              "kind": "DEEPER_DIVE",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Deeper dive: statistical mechanics",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Why do the laws hold? **Statistical mechanics**, built by Boltzmann, explains them from the) Tj
T* ( behavior of countless particles. Entropy counts the number of microscopic arrangements that look the same large-scale; ) Tj
T* (disordered states have vastly more arrangements, so systems drift toward them simply by probability. Boltzmann's ) Tj
T* (tombstone bears his equation, $S = k \\\\log W$, linking entropy $S$ to the number of microstates $W$ -- heat and ) Tj
T* (disorder, explained by counting.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "SUMMARY",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Summary",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "takeaways": [) Tj
T* (                  "Zeroth law: makes temperature meaningful \(thermometers work\).",) Tj
T* (                  "First law: energy is conserved, $\\\\Delta U = Q - W$ \('you can't win'\).",) Tj
T* (                  "Second law: total entropy never decreases \('you can't break even'\).",) Tj
T* (                  "Third law: absolute zero can never be fully reached.",) Tj
T* (                  "Statistical mechanics explains the laws by counting microscopic arrangements.") Tj
T* (                ],) Tj
T* (                "formulas": [) Tj
