T* (              "title": "The big idea",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "The **nucleus** contains **protons** \(positive\) and **neutrons** \(neutral\), bound by the ) Tj
T* (**strong nuclear force**, which overpowers the electric repulsion between protons at tiny range. The number of protons ) Tj
T* (\(the **atomic number**\) defines the element.\\n\\nUnstable nuclei undergo **radioactive decay**, emitting:\\n\\n- **Alpha** ) Tj
T* (\($\\\\alpha$\): a helium nucleus -- heavy, stopped by paper.\\n- **Beta** \($\\\\beta$\): an electron from a neutron turning ) Tj
T* (into a proton -- stopped by aluminum.\\n- **Gamma** \($\\\\gamma$\): a high-energy photon -- needs thick lead.\\n\\nDecay is ) Tj
T* (governed by a constant **half-life** -- the time for half a sample to decay -- regardless of the amount, which makes it ) Tj
T* (a precise clock for **radiometric dating**.\\n\\nThe energy comes from $E = mc^2$: the products weigh slightly *less* than) Tj
T* ( the original, and that missing mass \(the **mass defect**\) is released. **Fission** splits heavy nuclei; **fusion** ) Tj
T* (joins light ones -- the Sun's power source.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "WORKED_EXAMPLES",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Worked examples",) Tj
