T* (              "title": "The big idea",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "The **Standard Model** sorts the fundamental particles into two families:\\n\\n- **Quarks** ) Tj
T* (\(six types\) -- combine in threes to form protons and neutrons. A proton is two up quarks and one down.\\n- **Leptons** ) Tj
T* (\(six types\) -- include the **electron** and the elusive, nearly massless **neutrinos**.\\n\\nForces are carried by ) Tj
T* (**force-carrier particles** \(bosons\):\\n\\n- **Photon** -- electromagnetism.\\n- **Gluons** -- the strong force binding ) Tj
T* (quarks.\\n- **W and Z bosons** -- the weak force \(radioactive beta decay\).\\n\\nThe **Higgs boson**, confirmed in 2012, is ) Tj
T* (tied to the field that gives many particles their mass.\\n\\nWhat's missing: the Standard Model does **not** include ) Tj
T* (**gravity**, and it doesn't explain **dark matter** or **dark energy** -- which together outweigh ordinary matter ~20 to) Tj
T* ( 1. The deepest theory we have is still incomplete.") Tj
