T* (              "title": "Deeper dive: carbon dating",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Living things constantly take in carbon, including a steady trace of radioactive ) Tj
T* (**carbon-14**. When they die, intake stops and the carbon-14 decays with its ~5,700-year half-life. Measuring how much ) Tj
T* (remains gives the time since death. Carbon dating revolutionized archaeology -- dating the Dead Sea Scrolls, ?tzi the ) Tj
T* (Iceman, and cave art -- and earned Willard Libby the Nobel Prize. The randomness of single nuclei becomes, in bulk, an ) Tj
T* (exquisitely reliable clock.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
