T* (                "sub": "From holding a nucleus together to binding galaxies, every interaction in nature is one of just ) Tj
T* (four.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONTEXT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "The shortlist of nature",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Having met the particles of the Standard Model, we meet the **forces** between them. ) Tj
T* (Astonishingly, every push, pull, glow, and decay in the cosmos comes down to **four fundamental interactions**, each ) Tj
T* (with its own strength, range, and carrier particle.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONCEPT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "The big idea",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "The four fundamental forces, from strongest to weakest:\\n\\n- **Strong force** -- the ) Tj
T* (strongest; binds quarks into protons and neutrons and holds the nucleus together against electric repulsion. Very short ) Tj
T* (range \(nuclear size\). Carrier: **gluon**.\\n- **Electromagnetism** -- acts between electric charges; governs light, ) Tj
T* (chemistry, electronics, and all of everyday solidity. Infinite range, but attraction and repulsion. Carrier: ) Tj
T* (**photon**.\\n- **Weak force** -- responsible for certain radioactive decays and for the reactions that let stars fuse. ) Tj
T* (Extremely short range. Carriers: **W and Z bosons**.\\n- **Gravity** -- by far the weakest, but always attractive and ) Tj
T* (infinite in range, so it dominates at astronomical scales: planets, stars, galaxies. Carrier \(theorized\): the ) Tj
T* (**graviton**, not yet detected.\\n\\nA paradox: gravity rules the universe at large yet is fantastically feeble -- a tiny ) Tj
T* (magnet lifts a paperclip against the pull of the entire Earth. It dominates only because it's always attractive and ) Tj
T* (never cancels, while electric charges mostly balance out.\\n\\n**Unification** is a grand goal of physics. ) Tj
T* (Electromagnetism and the weak force have been merged into one **electroweak** force. Theories aim to unite the strong ) Tj
T* (force too, and ultimately gravity -- a 'theory of everything' -- but gravity stubbornly resists, the great unsolved ) Tj
T* (problem of fundamental physics.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "WORKED_EXAMPLES",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Worked examples",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "examples": [) Tj
T* (                  {) Tj
T* (                    "title": "Holding the nucleus",) Tj
