(      "lessons": [) Tj
T* (        {) Tj
T* (          "slug": "the-expanding-universe",) Tj
T* (          "title": "The Expanding Universe",) Tj
T* (          "tagline": "Everything is rushing apart",) Tj
T* (          "estMinutes": 16,) Tj
T* (          "xpReward": 200,) Tj
T* (          "difficulty": 5,) Tj
T* (          "sections": [) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "HERO",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "scene": "sun",) Tj
T* (                "headline": "Space Itself Is Stretching",) Tj
T* (                "sub": "Distant galaxies recede from us -- not through space, but because space between them is ) Tj
T* (growing.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONTEXT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "The cosmic discovery",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "In the 1920s Edwin Hubble found that almost every galaxy is moving **away** from us, and ) Tj
T* (the farther one is, the faster it flees. The startling conclusion: the **universe is expanding**. Run that expansion ) Tj
T* (backward and everything began, packed together, in a Big Bang.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONCEPT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "The big idea",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "**Hubble's law:** a galaxy's recession speed is proportional to its distance,\\n\\n$$v = ) Tj
T* (H_0\\\\,d,$$\\n\\nwhere $H_0$ is the **Hubble constant**. This is exactly what uniform **expansion of space** looks like ) Tj
T* (from any point -- there is no center; every observer sees everyone else receding.\\n\\nThe evidence is **cosmological ) Tj
T* (redshift**: light from distant galaxies is stretched to longer \(redder\) wavelengths as space expands while it travels. ) Tj
T* (More distant galaxies show greater redshift.\\n\\n- A common analogy: dots on an inflating balloon -- every dot moves away) Tj
T* ( from every other, with no special center.\\n- Reversing the expansion implies a hot, dense beginning ~13.8 billion years) Tj
T* ( ago.\\n- $1/H_0$ gives a rough estimate of the age of the universe.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "WORKED_EXAMPLES",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Worked examples",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "examples": [) Tj
T* (                  {) Tj
T* (                    "title": "Hubble's law",) Tj
T* (                    "problem": "Galaxy B is twice as far as galaxy A. How do their recession speeds compare?",) Tj
T* (                    "steps": [) Tj
T* (                      "$v = H_0 d$.",) Tj
T* (                      "Twice the distance -> twice the speed.") Tj
T* (                    ],) Tj
T* (                    "answer": "B recedes twice as fast.") Tj
T* (                  },) Tj
T* (                  {) Tj
T* (                    "title": "Redshift",) Tj
T* (                    "problem": "What does a galaxy's redshift tell us?",) Tj
T* (                    "steps": [) Tj
T* (                      "Light stretched by expansion.",) Tj
T* (                      "More redshift = farther/faster.") Tj
T* (                    ],) Tj
T* (                    "answer": "It is moving away; more shift, more distant.") Tj
T* (                  },) Tj
T* (                  {) Tj
T* (                    "title": "No center",) Tj
T* (                    "problem": "Where is the center of the expansion?",) Tj
T* (                    "steps": [) Tj
T* (                      "Every observer sees recession.",) Tj
T* (                      "Like a balloon's surface.") Tj
T* (                    ],) Tj
T* (                    "answer": "There is no center.") Tj
T* (                  }) Tj
T* (                ]) Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONCEPT_CHECK",) Tj
