T* (              "kind": "CONTEXT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Fixing the Big Bang's puzzles",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "The Big Bang theory is superbly supported, yet on its own it leaves puzzles: why is the ) Tj
T* (universe so uniform, and so precisely flat? **Cosmic inflation** -- a burst of exponential expansion in the first ) Tj
T* (instant -- was proposed to solve them, and made predictions later confirmed in the cosmic microwave background.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONCEPT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "The big idea",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "**Inflation** proposes that in the first tiny fraction of a second \(around $10^{-35}$ s ) Tj
T* (after the start\), the universe underwent a brief phase of **exponential expansion**, ballooning by a factor of at least ) Tj
T* ($10^{26}$ almost instantly -- space itself expanding faster than light \(which is allowed; no information travels through) Tj
T* ( it\).\\n\\nThis elegantly solves two puzzles:\\n\\n- **The horizon problem.** Opposite sides of the sky have nearly ) Tj
T* (identical temperature, yet seem too far apart to have ever exchanged heat. Inflation says they *were* in contact before ) Tj
T* (being stretched far apart -- explaining the uniformity.\\n- **The flatness problem.** The universe's geometry is observed) Tj
T* ( to be remarkably flat. Inflation stretches any initial curvature smooth, like inflating a balloon makes its surface ) Tj
T* (look flat up close.\\n\\nAnd a bonus: tiny **quantum fluctuations** in the early universe were stretched to cosmic scale ) Tj
T* (by inflation, becoming the slight density variations that later grew, under gravity, into **galaxies and galaxy ) Tj
T* (clusters**. The largest structures trace back to quantum jitters. These fluctuations are seen as faint temperature ) Tj
T* (ripples in the CMB, matching inflation's predictions remarkably well.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "WORKED_EXAMPLES",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Worked examples",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "examples": [) Tj
T* (                  {) Tj
T* (                    "title": "Horizon problem",) Tj
T* (                    "problem": "Why is the sky's temperature so uniform in all directions?",) Tj
T* (                    "steps": [) Tj
T* (                      "Distant regions seem never to have been in contact.",) Tj
T* (                      "Inflation says they were, before being stretched apart.") Tj
T* (                    ],) Tj
ET
