T* (              "title": "Deeper dive: can space expand faster than light?",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Special relativity caps how fast anything moves **through** space at $c$. But the expansion) Tj
T* ( of space itself isn't motion through space -- it's the stretching of the distances between things, and that has no ) Tj
T* (speed limit. During inflation, and even today for very distant galaxies, the space between us and them grows so fast ) Tj
T* (that those galaxies recede faster than light and their future light can never reach us. The cosmic speed limit applies ) Tj
T* (to objects, not to the stage they sit on.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
