(              "kind": "CONTEXT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "The end of the journey",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "We began at the Moon and have reached the edge of space and time. The final question is the) Tj
T* ( grandest: how does it all end? The answer turns on the contest between gravity, pulling everything together, and **dark) Tj
T* ( energy**, pushing it apart.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONCEPT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "The big idea",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "The universe is expanding \(Hubble's law, $v = H d$\). Its long-term fate depends on whether ) Tj
T* (gravity or **dark energy** wins:\\n\\n- **Big Crunch** -- if gravity dominated, expansion would halt and reverse, ) Tj
T* (collapsing everything back together. Observations now make this unlikely.\\n- **Big Freeze \(Heat Death\)** -- if expansion) Tj
T* ( continues forever, stars burn out, galaxies drift apart, and the universe cools toward maximum entropy and darkness. ) Tj
T* (This is the favored fate.\\n- **Big Rip** -- if dark energy strengthens over time, expansion could accelerate so ) Tj
T* (violently it eventually tears apart galaxies, stars, and even atoms.\\n\\nThe stunning discovery of 1998 -- that the ) Tj
T* (expansion is **accelerating**, not slowing -- revealed that dark energy \(about **68%** of the universe\) currently ) Tj
T* (dominates. Unless its nature changes, the cosmos faces a cold, dark, ever-emptier future: the **Big Freeze**.\\n\\nIt's a ) Tj
T* (humbling endpoint, but not a gloomy one. On the scale of human lives, the universe is young and brilliant, full of stars) Tj
T* ( being born. Understanding its arc -- from a hot dense beginning to a vast cold future -- is one of the great ) Tj
T* (achievements of the human mind, and the reason the journey from the Moon to the edge of the cosmos was worth taking.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
