T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Dark energy is the deepest mystery in physics. It behaves like an energy built into space ) Tj
T* (itself, pushing it apart, and its measured value is bafflingly small compared with naive quantum predictions -- off by ) Tj
T* (some 120 orders of magnitude, the worst estimate in the history of science. Is it Einstein's 'cosmological constant,' a ) Tj
T* (new field, or a sign that gravity itself needs revising on cosmic scales? Whoever answers will rewrite physics. The ) Tj
