T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONCEPT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "The big idea",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Counting sounds easy -- but there is a secret rule that makes it work. The rule is **one ) Tj
T* (number for one thing**. This is called *one-to-one counting*.\\n\\nWhen you count the ducks, you point at **one** duck and) Tj
T* ( say **\\"one.\\"** You point at the **next** duck and say **\\"two.\\"** Then **\\"three.\\"** Each duck gets exactly one ) Tj
T* (number, and you never skip a duck or count the same duck twice.\\n\\nThe number words always go in the same ) Tj
T* (order:\\n\\n**one, two, three, four, five, six, seven, eight, nine, ten.**\\n\\nThere is a second secret, and it is a big ) Tj
T* (one. The **last number you say tells you how many there are altogether.** If you count three ducks -- \\"one, two, ) Tj
