T* (                "scene": "park",) Tj
T* (                "headline": "A Park Full of Shapes",) Tj
T* (                "sub": "The pond is a circle. The picnic blanket is a square. The flag on the hill is a triangle. Once ) Tj
T* (you spot shapes, you'll see them everywhere.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONTEXT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "You're standing on the picnic lawn",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Spread out your picnic blanket and look at its edges. Four straight sides, four corners -- ) Tj
T* (that's a **square**. Glance at the round pond: no corners at all, just one smooth curve -- a **circle**. Up on the hill,) Tj
T* ( a flag makes a **triangle** with three sides.\\n\\nShapes are the building blocks of everything we draw and build. ) Tj
T* (Knowing their names and what makes each one special is the start of **geometry** -- the math of shapes and space. And it) Tj
T* ( all begins right here in the park.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONCEPT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Meet the shapes",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "We tell shapes apart by counting two things: their **sides** \(the straight edges\) and their) Tj
T* ( **corners** \(where two sides meet, also called *vertices*\).\\n\\n- **Circle** -- perfectly round. It has **0 sides** and ) Tj
T* (**0 corners**, just one smooth curve. Think of a wheel, a coin, or the Sun.\\n- **Triangle** -- **3 sides** and **3 ) Tj
T* (corners**. *Tri* means three! Think of a slice of pizza or a party hat.\\n- **Square** -- **4 sides** and **4 corners**, ) Tj
T* (and all four sides are the **same length**. Think of a cracker or a window pane.\\n- **Rectangle** -- **4 sides** and **4) Tj
T* ( corners**, but the sides come in **two long and two short**. A door and a phone are rectangles.\\n\\nHere's a clever ) Tj
T* (idea: a **square is a special rectangle** where every side happens to be equal. So all squares are rectangles, but not ) Tj
T* (all rectangles are squares!\\n\\nShapes can be **big or small, and turned any way**, and they are still the same shape. A ) Tj
T* (triangle balanced on its point is still a triangle. Turning a shape never changes what it is -- only its sides and ) Tj
T* (corners decide its name.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
ET
endstream
