T* (                "scene": "park",) Tj
T* (                "headline": "What Comes Next?",) Tj
T* (                "sub": "Red tulip, yellow tulip, red tulip, yellow tulip... The flower beds of the park are full of ) Tj
T* (patterns waiting to be cracked.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONTEXT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "You're standing by the flower beds",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Walk along the garden path. The gardener planted the tulips in a special order: **red, ) Tj
T* (yellow, red, yellow, red, yellow**. Can you guess what color comes next?\\n\\nThat repeating order is called a ) Tj
T* (**pattern**. Patterns are everywhere -- in the stripes on a bee, the days of the week, the tiles on a floor, and the ) Tj
T* (beat of a song.\\n\\nFinding patterns is one of the most powerful things a mathematician does. When you spot a pattern, ) Tj
T* (you can **predict what comes next** -- even far into the future. That's a kind of magic you'll use for the rest of your ) Tj
T* (life in math.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONCEPT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "How patterns work",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "A **pattern** is something that **repeats in the same order again and again**. The part ) Tj
T* (that repeats is called the **unit** -- the little chunk that keeps coming back.\\n\\nMathematicians give patterns ) Tj
T* (nicknames using letters. Each new thing gets a letter:\\n\\n- **A B A B** -- like *red, yellow, red, yellow*. The unit is ) Tj
T* (\\"A B\\" and it repeats.\\n- **A A B A A B** -- like *clap, clap, stomp, clap, clap, stomp*. The unit is \\"A A B.\\"\\n- **A) Tj
T* ( B C A B C** -- like *red, yellow, blue, red, yellow, blue*. The unit is \\"A B C.\\"\\n\\nTo figure out **what comes ) Tj
T* (next**, do three things:\\n\\n1. **Find the unit** -- the part that repeats.\\n2. **Check where you are** in the unit.\\n3. ) Tj
T* (**Say the next piece** of the unit.\\n\\nFor *red, yellow, red, yellow, red, ___* the unit is \\"red, yellow.\\" We just ) Tj
T* (said red, so next comes **yellow**.\\n\\nPatterns don't have to be colors. They can be **shapes** \(circle, square, circle,) Tj
T* ( square\), **sounds** \(loud, soft, loud, soft\), **movements** \(jump, spin, jump, spin\), or **numbers** \(1, 2, 1, 2\). The ) Tj
T* (idea is always the same: find the repeating unit, and you can predict forever.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "SIMULATION",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Try it: pattern maker",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
ET
