T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONTEXT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "You're standing at the snack stand",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Two squirrels-in-training, Pip and Bo, empty their pockets at the snack stand. Pip has 5 ) Tj
T* (acorns. Bo has 3 acorns. Who has **more**?\\n\\nEvery day we compare amounts. Who has more stickers? Are there enough cups) Tj
T* ( for everyone? Is this pile bigger than that one? Learning to say **more**, **less**, and **equal** turns counting into ) Tj
T* (comparing -- and comparing is the doorway to adding, subtracting, and one day even algebra.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONCEPT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Comparing amounts",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "There are three ways two amounts can compare:\\n\\n- **More** \(greater\) -- one group has a ) Tj
T* (bigger amount.\\n- **Less** \(fewer\) -- one group has a smaller amount.\\n- **Equal** \(the same\) -- both groups have ) Tj
T* (exactly the same amount.\\n\\nHow do we tell? Two ways:\\n\\n**1. Match them up.** Line up Pip's acorns next to Bo's, one ) Tj
T* (for one. If Pip still has some left over after every one of Bo's is matched, then Pip has **more**. If they match ) Tj
T* (perfectly with none left over, they are **equal**.\\n\\n**2. Count and compare.** Count each group. The bigger number is ) Tj
T* (more. Pip has 5, Bo has 3. Since **5 is more than 3**, Pip has more -- and Bo has **less**.\\n\\nIn counting order -- 1, ) Tj
T* (2, 3, 4, 5, 6... -- numbers that come **later** are **bigger**. So 5 comes after 3, which means 5 is more than 3. The ) Tj
T* (number 8 is more than 6 because 8 comes later when you count.\\n\\nMathematicians even have tiny symbols for this, which ) Tj
T* (you'll meet soon:\\n\\n- the same as: **=** \(5 = 5\)\\n- more than: **>** \(5 > 3\)\\n- less than: **<** \(3 < 5\)\\n\\nFor now, ) Tj
T* (the words *more*, *less*, and *equal* are your trusty tools.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "SIMULATION",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Try it: the balance",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "simId": "compare-balance",) Tj
T* (                "intro": "Drop acorns onto each side of the balance scale. The heavier side tips down -- that's the side) Tj
T* ( with more. Make the two sides equal to balance it!") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
ET
endstream
