T* (                "headline": "Putting Things Together",) Tj
T* (                "sub": "Three pencils on your desk, four more from a friend -- how many now? Addition is the math of ) Tj
T* (joining amounts into one total.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONTEXT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "At the classroom door",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "School has begun on Elementary School St. The morning bell rings and the lunch monitor ) Tj
T* (needs a count: 5 children are already at the table, and 3 more walk in. **How many in all?**\\n\\nWhenever we **join** two) Tj
T* ( amounts and ask \\"how many altogether?\\", we are doing **addition** -- the first of the four great operations of ) Tj
T* (arithmetic. Get addition solid here, and every later idea -- subtraction, multiplication, even algebra -- will build on ) Tj
T* (it.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONCEPT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "The big idea",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "**Addition** combines two \(or more\) amounts into a single total. We write it with the ) Tj
T* (**plus sign** $+$, and the answer is called the **sum**.\\n\\n$$5 + 3 = 8$$\\n\\nRead it as *\\"five plus three equals ) Tj
T* (eight.\\"* The **equals sign** $=$ means *\\"is the same amount as\\"* -- the left side and the right side are worth ) Tj
T* (exactly the same.\\n\\nThree things worth knowing:\\n\\n- **Counting on.** To find $5 + 3$, start at 5 and count three more:) Tj
T* ( 6, 7, 8. The last number is the sum.\\n- **Order doesn't matter.** $5 + 3$ and $3 + 5$ both equal 8. Swapping the order ) Tj
T* (never changes the sum. \(Mathematicians call this the *commutative property*.\)\\n- **Adding zero changes nothing.** $7 + 0) Tj
T* ( = 7$. Joining \\"nothing\\" leaves the amount the same.\\n\\nYou can picture addition as **jumps to the right on a number ) Tj
T* (line**: start at the first number, then hop forward by the second.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "SIMULATION",) Tj
