T* (                "sub": "You had 8 crayons and lent 3 to a friend. How many are left? Subtraction is the math of taking ) Tj
T* (away and comparing.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONTEXT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "At the supply cupboard",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "The art teacher counts 9 glue sticks in the cupboard. The class uses 4. **How many are ) Tj
T* (left?** And when two reading groups have 9 and 6 books, **how many more** does the bigger group have?\\n\\nBoth questions ) Tj
T* (are answered by **subtraction** -- the partner of addition. Subtraction tells us what remains after taking some away, ) Tj
T* (and it tells us the gap, or *difference*, between two amounts.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONCEPT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "The big idea",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "**Subtraction** takes one amount away from another, or finds the **difference** between ) Tj
T* (them. We write it with the **minus sign** $-$, and the answer is called the **difference**.\\n\\n$$8 - 3 = 5$$\\n\\nRead it ) Tj
T* (as *\\"eight minus three equals five.\\"*\\n\\nKey facts:\\n\\n- **Counting back.** To find $8 - 3$, start at 8 and count back) Tj
T* ( three: 7, 6, 5. The number you land on is the difference.\\n- **Order matters.** Unlike addition, $7 - 2$ is *not* the ) Tj
T* (same as $2 - 7$. Subtraction is **not** commutative -- you must keep the larger amount first \(for now\).\\n- **Subtracting) Tj
T* ( zero changes nothing:** $6 - 0 = 6$. And any number minus itself is zero: $6 - 6 = 0$.\\n- **Subtraction undoes ) Tj
T* (addition.** Since $4 + 5 = 9$, it must be that $9 - 5 = 4$. They are *inverse* operations -- this is your best way to ) Tj
T* (**check** a subtraction.\\n\\nOn a number line, subtracting is **jumps to the left**: start at the first number and hop ) Tj
T* (backward by the second.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "SIMULATION",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Try it: the number line",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "simId": "number-line",) Tj
T* (                "intro": "Set the start number, choose Subtract, and pick an amount. Each jump moves one unit to the ) Tj
T* (left -- the spot you land on is the difference.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "WORKED_EXAMPLES",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Worked examples",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "examples": [) Tj
