T* (carry them over.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONTEXT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Stacking the library carts",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "The school library has 27 books on one cart and 15 on another. To shelve them, the ) Tj
T* (librarian needs the total. With numbers this size, counting on your fingers is slow -- so we use place value to add ) Tj
T* (**column by column**, a method that scales up to any size of number.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONCEPT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "The big idea",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "To add two-digit numbers, line them up by place -- **ones under ones, tens under tens** -- ) Tj
T* (and add each column, starting from the **ones** on the right.\\n\\n**When a column doesn't reach ten** \(no regrouping\), ) Tj
T* (just add each column:\\n\\n$$23 + 14: \\\\quad 3 + 4 = 7 \\\\ \(\\\\text{ones}\), \\\\quad 2 + 1 = 3 \\\\ \(\\\\text{tens}\) ) Tj
T* (\\\\;\\\\Rightarrow\\\\; 37.$$\\n\\n**When the ones reach ten or more**, you must **regroup** \(also called **carrying**\). Ten ) Tj
T* (ones bundle into one ten, which you carry into the tens column:\\n\\n$$27 + 15: \\\\quad 7 + 5 = 12.$$\\n\\nThat's 1 ten and 2) Tj
T* ( ones -- write the **2** in the ones place and **carry the 1** ten on top of the tens column. Then add the tens, ) Tj
T* (*including the carry*:\\n\\n$$2 + 1 + 1 = 4 \\\\;\\\\Rightarrow\\\\; 42.$$\\n\\nThe rule in one line: **add each column right to ) Tj
T* (left, and whenever a column hits 10 or more, carry the extra ten to the next column.** It's the same \\"ten ones make one) Tj
T* ( ten\\" bundling from place value -- now put to work.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "SIMULATION",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Try it: the number line",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "simId": "number-line",) Tj
T* (                "intro": "Try smaller sums on the number line to build intuition: set a start, choose Add, and jump. The) Tj
T* ( column method is just a faster way to do these same jumps for bigger numbers.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "WORKED_EXAMPLES",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Worked examples",) Tj
