T* (                "headline": "Fractions in Disguise",) Tj
T* (                "sub": "Half a loaf, 0.5 of a loaf, 50% of a loaf -- same amount, three notations. Prices and discounts ) Tj
T* (speak all three.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONTEXT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Reading the price tags",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "The bakery's sign says muffins are **25% off** and a loaf costs **$3.50**. Decimals and ) Tj
T* (percents are how money and discounts are written -- and underneath, they're just fractions. Learning to switch between ) Tj
T* (all three is one of the most useful skills in everyday math.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONCEPT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "The big idea",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "**Decimals** extend place value past the ones, into tenths, hundredths, and ) Tj
T* (beyond:\\n\\n$$0.5 = \\\\frac{5}{10} = \\\\frac12, \\\\qquad 0.25 = \\\\frac{25}{100} = \\\\frac14, \\\\qquad 0.75 = \\\\frac{75}{100} =) Tj
T* ( \\\\frac34.$$\\n\\nThe first digit after the dot is **tenths**, the second is **hundredths**. To turn a fraction into a ) Tj
T* (decimal, **divide** the top by the bottom: $\\\\tfrac34 = 3 \\\\div 4 = 0.75$.\\n\\n**Percent** means **\\"per hundred\\"** -- ) Tj
T* (the symbol $\\\\%$ literally stands for $/100$:\\n\\n$$50\\\\% = \\\\frac{50}{100} = 0.5, \\\\qquad 25\\\\% = \\\\frac{25}{100} = ) Tj
T* (0.25.$$\\n\\nSo the three forms convert easily:\\n\\n- **Fraction -> decimal:** divide top by bottom.\\n- **Decimal -> ) Tj
T* (percent:** multiply by 100 \(move the dot two places right\): $0.5 \\\\to 50\\\\%$.\\n- **Percent -> decimal:** divide by 100 ) Tj
T* (\(move the dot two places left\): $75\\\\% \\\\to 0.75$.\\n\\nMemorising a few anchors makes this instant: $\\\\tfrac12 = 0.5 = ) Tj
T* (50\\\\%$, $\\\\tfrac14 = 0.25 = 25\\\\%$, $\\\\tfrac34 = 0.75 = 75\\\\%$, $\\\\tfrac{1}{10} = 0.1 = 10\\\\%$.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
