T* (              "title": "Deeper dive: repeating decimals",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Not every fraction gives a clean, ending decimal. Try $\\\\tfrac13 = 1 \\\\div 3 = ) Tj
T* (0.3333\\\\ldots$ -- the 3s never stop. We write this as $0.\\\\overline{3}$, with a bar over the repeating part. Fractions ) Tj
T* (whose denominators \(in lowest terms\) are built only from 2s and 5s give *terminating* decimals like $0.25$; all others ) Tj
T* (**repeat** forever in a pattern. Remarkably, every repeating decimal can be turned back into an exact fraction -- so ) Tj
T* (fractions and decimals describe exactly the same set of numbers, the *rationals*.") Tj
