(            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "DEEPER_DIVE",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Deeper dive: percent is reversible",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "A surprising fact: **$p\\\\%$ of $q$ equals $q\\\\%$ of $p$**. So $8\\\\%$ of $50$ is the same as) Tj
T* ( $50\\\\%$ of $8$ -- and the second is obviously $4$! This works because both are $\\\\dfrac{p \\\\times q}{100}$. When one ) Tj
T* (number is an easy percent \(like 50 or 25 or 10\), flip the problem to make it trivial. It's a favourite trick for fast ) Tj
T* (mental math and a neat reminder that multiplication doesn't care about order.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
