T* (                "headline": "How Much It Changed",) Tj
T* (                "sub": "A price drops from $50 to $40 -- that's a 20% decrease. Percent change measures growth and ) Tj
T* (discounts alike.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONTEXT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "From sale tags to statistics",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Prices rise and fall, populations grow, scores improve. To compare these fairly, we use ) Tj
T* (**percent change** -- the change measured against where you started. A $10 drop means very different things on a $20 ) Tj
T* (item versus a $1000 item; percent change captures that.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONCEPT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "The big idea",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "**Percent change** measures how much a quantity grew or shrank, relative to its ) Tj
T* (**original** value:\\n\\n$$\\\\text{percent change} = \\\\frac{\\\\text{change}}{\\\\text{original}} \\\\times 100\\\\%.$$\\n\\nIf the ) Tj
T* (value went **up**, it's a percent **increase**; if **down**, a percent **decrease**. The change is always compared to ) Tj
T* (the *starting* amount, not the new one.\\n\\nExample: a price rises from $50 to $60. The change is $10$, ) Tj
T* (so\\n\\n$$\\\\frac{10}{50} \\\\times 100\\\\% = 20\\\\%\\\\ \\\\text{increase}.$$\\n\\n**Discounts and markups** are percent change ) Tj
T* (applied to prices:\\n\\n- A **discount** lowers the price: a $25\\\\%$ discount on $80 removes $25\\\\%$ of $80 = \\\\$20$, so ) Tj
T* (you pay $80 - 20 = \\\\$60$.\\n- A **markup** raises it: a $20\\\\%$ markup on $50 adds $\\\\$10$, giving $\\\\$60$.\\n\\nA ) Tj
T* (shortcut for sale prices: paying after a $25\\\\%$ discount means paying $100\\\\% - 25\\\\% = 75\\\\%$ of the original. So the ) Tj
T* (sale price is $0.75 \\\\times 80 = \\\\$60$ in one step.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "SIMULATION",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Try it: visualize the percent",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "simId": "fraction-pie",) Tj
T* (                "intro": "Use the pie to picture the percent you're keeping or removing. A 30%-off item means you shade ) Tj
T* (and pay the other 70% -- see that 70% as a slice of the whole.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
ET
