T* (              "title": "Deeper dive: why increases and decreases don't cancel",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Here's a trap: a price goes **up 50%** then **down 50%** -- are you back where you started?) Tj
T* ( No! Start at $100; up 50% gives $150; down 50% of *150* removes $75, leaving **$75**. The catch is that each percent is) Tj
T* ( taken from a *different* base. This is why a stock that drops 50% must then *gain 100%* just to recover, and why ) Tj
T* ('percent off' and 'percent on' never simply cancel. Always check what the percent is a percentage *of*.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
