T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "scene": "city",) Tj
T* (                "headline": "A Letter for the Unknown",) Tj
T* (                "sub": "When you don't yet know a number, give it a name. That single idea -- the variable -- opens the ) Tj
T* (door to all of algebra.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONTEXT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "On the steps of City Hall",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "A notice on the plaza board reads: \\"Admission is \\\\$2 per person.\\" How much for a group? ) Tj
T* (You can't answer with one number -- it depends on the size of the group. So we let a **letter** stand in for the unknown) Tj
T* ( count and write a rule that works for *any* group.\\n\\nThat letter is a **variable**, and the rule is an **expression**.) Tj
T* ( They are the language algebra uses to talk about quantities before we know their values.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONCEPT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "The big idea",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "A **variable** is a symbol -- usually a letter like $x$ or $n$ -- that stands for a number ) Tj
T* (we don't know yet or that can change.\\n\\nAn **expression** combines numbers, variables, and operations but has **no ) Tj
T* (equals sign**. It names a quantity:\\n\\n$$2n, \\\\qquad x + 5, \\\\qquad 3a - 7.$$\\n\\n- A **term** is a single piece: in $3a ) Tj
T* (- 7$ the terms are $3a$ and $-7$.\\n- A **coefficient** is the number multiplying a variable: in $3a$ the coefficient is ) Tj
T* ($3$.\\n- A **constant** is a plain number, like the $-7$.\\n\\nTo **evaluate** an expression, substitute a value for the ) Tj
T* (variable and compute. If $n = 4$:\\n\\n$$2n = 2\(4\) = 8.$$\\n\\nWriting $2n$ means $2 \\\\times n$ -- in algebra a number next ) Tj
T* (to a variable always means multiply.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "WORKED_EXAMPLES",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Worked examples",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "examples": [) Tj
T* (                  {) Tj
T* (                    "title": "Evaluate an expression",) Tj
T* (                    "problem": "Evaluate $3x + 2$ when $x = 5$.",) Tj
ET
