T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONCEPT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "The big idea",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "An **equation** says two expressions are equal: $x + 7 = 12$. To **solve** it is to find ) Tj
T* (the value of the variable that makes the statement true.\\n\\nThe golden rule: **whatever you do to one side, do to the ) Tj
T* (other.** This keeps the scale balanced. To isolate the variable, undo what's done to it using the **inverse ) Tj
T* (operation**:\\n\\n- Addition is undone by subtraction \(and vice versa\).\\n- Multiplication is undone by division \(and vice ) Tj
T* (versa\).\\n\\nTo solve $x + 7 = 12$, subtract $7$ from **both** sides:\\n\\n$$x + 7 - 7 = 12 - 7 \\\\;\\\\Rightarrow\\\\; x = ) Tj
T* (5.$$\\n\\n**Check** by substituting back: $5 + 7 = 12$. [x] Always check -- it catches mistakes instantly.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
