T* (                "markdown": "The same two-step logic rearranges **formulas**. To solve $y = mx + b$ for $x$, treat $y$, ) Tj
T* ($m$, $b$ as known: subtract $b$ from both sides to get $y - b = mx$, then divide by $m$ to get $x = \\\\dfrac{y - b}{m}$. ) Tj
T* (This is exactly how scientists rearrange equations to isolate whatever quantity they need -- the skill scales all the ) Tj
T* (way to physics and calculus.") Tj
