T* (              "title": "The big idea",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "**Words -> symbols.** Watch the keywords:\\n\\n- 'sum', 'more than', 'increased by' -> $+$\\n-) Tj
T* ( 'difference', 'less than', 'decreased by' -> $-$\\n- 'product', 'times', 'of' -> $\\\\times$\\n- 'quotient', 'per', ) Tj
T* ('divided by' -> $\\\\div$\\n\\n'Three less than twice a number $x$' is $2x - 3$ \(note the order: subtract from ) Tj
T* ($2x$\).\\n\\n**Symbols -> graph.** A linear expression $mx + b$, drawn as $y = mx + b$, is a straight line:\\n\\n- $b$ is the) Tj
T* ( **$y$-intercept** -- where the line crosses the vertical axis \($x = 0$\).\\n- $m$ is the **slope** -- how much $y$ ) Tj
T* (changes for each step of $1$ in $x$.\\n\\nFor $y = 2x - 1$: start at $-1$ on the $y$-axis, then rise $2$ for every $1$ ) Tj
T* (across. A positive slope rises left-to-right; a negative slope falls.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
