T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONCEPT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "The big idea",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "An **angle** measures the turn between two rays from a shared vertex, in **degrees** ) Tj
T* (\($^\\\\circ$\).\\n\\n- **Acute**: less than $90^\\\\circ$. **Right**: exactly $90^\\\\circ$. **Obtuse**: between $90^\\\\circ$ and ) Tj
T* ($180^\\\\circ$. **Straight**: $180^\\\\circ$.\\n\\nThe key relationships:\\n\\n- **Complementary** angles sum to $90^\\\\circ$.\\n-) Tj
T* ( **Supplementary** angles sum to $180^\\\\circ$.\\n- Angles on a **straight line** sum to $180^\\\\circ$; angles **around a ) Tj
T* (point** sum to $360^\\\\circ$.\\n- When two lines cross, the opposite \(**vertical**\) angles are **equal**.\\n\\nThese let you) Tj
T* ( chase missing angles: if one angle on a line is $130^\\\\circ$, the angle beside it is $180^\\\\circ - 130^\\\\circ = ) Tj
T* (50^\\\\circ$.") Tj
