T* (              "kind": "DEEPER_DIVE",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Deeper dive: the distance formula",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Plot two points on a grid. The horizontal gap is $\\\\Delta x$, the vertical gap $\\\\Delta y$,) Tj
T* ( and the straight-line distance between them is the hypotenuse of a right triangle with those legs. So $d = ) Tj
T* (\\\\sqrt{\\\\Delta x^2 + \\\\Delta y^2}$ -- the **distance formula** is just the Pythagorean theorem in coordinates. Extend it) Tj
T* ( to three dimensions and you get $d = \\\\sqrt{\\\\Delta x^2 + \\\\Delta y^2 + \\\\Delta z^2}$, the length of a vector -- a tool) Tj
T* ( you'll use constantly in physics.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "SUMMARY",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Summary",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
