T* (              "title": "Deeper dive: standard deviation",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "The most-used measure of spread is the **standard deviation** $\\\\sigma$ -- roughly, the ) Tj
T* (typical distance of a value from the mean. You compute it by averaging the squared distances from the mean \(the ) Tj
T* (**variance**\) and taking the square root. Squaring keeps everything positive and weights big deviations more heavily. ) Tj
T* (Standard deviation is the backbone of the bell curve, opinion-poll margins of error, and quality control in ) Tj
T* (engineering.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
