T* (                "sub": "Probability puts a number on chance: 0 means never, 1 means certain, and everything interesting ) Tj
T* (lives in between.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONTEXT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Pricing the odds",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Every bet, insurance policy, and weather forecast rests on **probability** -- a precise ) Tj
T* (number for how likely an event is. Get the probability right and you price risk correctly; get it wrong and you lose. ) Tj
T* (The basics are simple counting, but they power a vast field.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONCEPT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "The big idea",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "The **probability** of an event is a number from $0$ \(impossible\) to $1$ \(certain\). For ) Tj
T* (equally likely outcomes:\\n\\n$$P\(\\\\text{event}\) = \\\\frac{\\\\text{favorable outcomes}}{\\\\text{total ) Tj
T* (outcomes}}.$$\\n\\nExamples:\\n\\n- A fair coin: $P\(\\\\text{heads}\) = \\\\tfrac12 = 0.5$.\\n- A fair die: $P\(4\) = \\\\tfrac16$; ) Tj
T* ($P\(\\\\text{even}\) = \\\\tfrac{3}{6} = \\\\tfrac12$.\\n\\nThe **complement** rule: $P\(\\\\text{not } A\) = 1 - P\(A\)$. If rain is ) Tj
T* ($0.3$ likely, no-rain is $0.7$.\\n\\nFor **independent** events \(one doesn't affect the other\), multiply: $P\(A \\\\text{ and) Tj
T* ( } B\) = P\(A\)\\\\times P\(B\)$. Two heads in a row: $\\\\tfrac12 \\\\times \\\\tfrac12 = \\\\tfrac14$.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "WORKED_EXAMPLES",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Worked examples",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "examples": [) Tj
T* (                  {) Tj
T* (                    "title": "Single die",) Tj
T* (                    "problem": "Find $P\(\\\\text{even}\)$ on a fair die.",) Tj
T* (                    "steps": [) Tj
T* (                      "Even outcomes: 2, 4, 6 -> 3 of them.",) Tj
T* (                      "$3/6$.") Tj
T* (                    ],) Tj
T* (                    "answer": "$P = \\\\tfrac12 = 0.5$.") Tj
T* (                  },) Tj
T* (                  {) Tj
T* (                    "title": "Complement",) Tj
T* (                    "problem": "If $P\(\\\\text{rain}\) = 0.3$, find $P\(\\\\text{no rain}\)$.",) Tj
T* (                    "steps": [) Tj
T* (                      "Use $1 - P$.",) Tj
T* (                      "$1 - 0.3 = 0.7$.") Tj
T* (                    ],) Tj
T* (                    "answer": "$0.7$.") Tj
T* (                  },) Tj
T* (                  {) Tj
T* (                    "title": "Two coins",) Tj
T* (                    "problem": "Find $P\(\\\\text{two heads}\)$ tossing two fair coins.",) Tj
T* (                    "steps": [) Tj
T* (                      "Independent: multiply.",) Tj
T* (                      "$\\\\tfrac12 \\\\times \\\\tfrac12$.") Tj
T* (                    ],) Tj
T* (                    "answer": "$\\\\tfrac14 = 0.25$.") Tj
T* (                  }) Tj
T* (                ]) Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
