T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Probability predicts the **long run**, not the next trial. A fair coin has ) Tj
T* ($P\(\\\\text{heads}\) = 0.5$, but ten tosses might give seven heads. The **law of large numbers** says that as the number of) Tj
T* ( trials grows, the observed fraction of heads converges to $0.5$. This is why casinos and insurers -- who run millions ) Tj
T* (of trials -- can profit reliably from probabilities, even though any single outcome is uncertain.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
