T* (              "kind": "CONTEXT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Steady machines",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "A conveyor that adds the same number of parts each minute, a tank that drains at a fixed ) Tj
T* (rate -- these are **linear** processes. Their defining feature is a **constant rate of change**, which shows up as a ) Tj
T* (straight-line graph. Linear functions are the simplest and most common model in all of engineering.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONCEPT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "The big idea",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "A **linear function** has the form\\n\\n$$f\(x\) = mx + b,$$\\n\\nwhose graph is a straight ) Tj
T* (line.\\n\\n- $m$ is the **slope** -- the change in output per unit change in input: $m = \\\\dfrac{\\\\Delta y}{\\\\Delta x} = ) Tj
T* (\\\\dfrac{\\\\text{rise}}{\\\\text{run}}$.\\n- $b$ is the **$y$-intercept** -- the output when $x = 0$, where the line crosses ) Tj
T* (the vertical axis.\\n\\nSlope between two points $\(x_1, y_1\)$ and $\(x_2, y_2\)$:\\n\\n$$m = \\\\frac{y_2 - y_1}{x_2 - ) Tj
T* (x_1}.$$\\n\\nA positive slope rises, a negative slope falls, a zero slope is horizontal. The bigger $|m|$, the steeper the) Tj
T* ( line.") Tj
