T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "In a right triangle, label the sides relative to an angle $\\\\theta$: the **opposite**, the ) Tj
T* (**adjacent**, and the **hypotenuse**. The three trig ratios are:\\n\\n$$\\\\sin\\\\theta = \\\\frac{\\\\text{opp}}{\\\\text{hyp}}, ) Tj
T* (\\\\qquad \\\\cos\\\\theta = \\\\frac{\\\\text{adj}}{\\\\text{hyp}}, \\\\qquad \\\\tan\\\\theta = ) Tj
T* (\\\\frac{\\\\text{opp}}{\\\\text{adj}}.$$\\n\\nRemember **SOH-CAH-TOA**. Since $\\\\tan\\\\theta = \\\\dfrac{\\\\text{opp}}{\\\\text{adj}}) Tj
T* ( = \\\\dfrac{\\\\sin\\\\theta}{\\\\cos\\\\theta}$, the three are linked.\\n\\nKey reference values:\\n\\n- $\\\\sin 30^\\\\circ = ) Tj
T* (\\\\tfrac12$, $\\\\cos 60^\\\\circ = \\\\tfrac12$.\\n- $\\\\sin 45^\\\\circ = \\\\cos 45^\\\\circ = \\\\tfrac{\\\\sqrt2}{2} \\\\approx ) Tj
T* (0.707$.\\n- $\\\\tan 45^\\\\circ = 1$.\\n\\nGiven an angle and one side, these ratios find the others; given two sides, the ) Tj
T* (**inverse** functions \($\\\\sin^{-1}$, etc.\) recover the angle.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
