T* (              "title": "Waves under the bridge",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Watch the water below the observatory bridge rise and fall in a smooth, repeating swell. ) Tj
T* (Plot a point's height over time and you get the **sine curve** -- nature's signature for anything that repeats: ) Tj
T* (heartbeats, radio, AC power, the seasons.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONCEPT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "The big idea",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "As $\\\\theta$ runs around the unit circle, the $y$-coordinate traces $y = \\\\sin\\\\theta$ and ) Tj
T* (the $x$-coordinate traces $y = \\\\cos\\\\theta$.\\n\\nBoth are **periodic** with period $2\\\\pi$ -- they repeat every full ) Tj
T* (turn -- and oscillate between $-1$ and $1$.\\n\\n- **Amplitude**: the peak height. For $y = A\\\\sin x$ it is $|A|$.\\n- ) Tj
T* (**Period**: the length of one cycle. For $y = \\\\sin\(Bx\)$ it is $\\\\dfrac{2\\\\pi}{B}$ -- a larger $B$ squeezes the wave.\\n-) Tj
T* ( $\\\\sin x$ starts at $0$ and rises; $\\\\cos x$ starts at its peak $1$. Cosine is just sine shifted left by ) Tj
T* ($\\\\tfrac{\\\\pi}{2}$.\\n\\nThese two controls -- amplitude and period -- let a sine wave model a pure tone, a tide, or an ) Tj
T* (alternating current.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
