T* (              "title": "Deeper dive: phase and Fourier",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Adding a **phase shift** slides a wave sideways: $\\\\sin\(x - \\\\phi\)$. With amplitude, ) Tj
T* (period, and phase you can place a sine wave anywhere. The astonishing **Fourier theorem** then says *any* repeating ) Tj
T* (signal -- a square wave, a violin note, a heartbeat -- is a sum of pure sines and cosines of different frequencies. That) Tj
T* ( decomposition powers MP3s, image compression, and nearly all of signal processing.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
