T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Compound interest at rate $100\\\\%$ split into more and more periods approaches a limit: ) Tj
T* ($\\\\left\(1 + \\\\tfrac1n\\\\right\)^n \\\\to e$ as $n \\\\to \\\\infty$. The function $e^x$ is the unique exponential whose **rate ) Tj
T* (of growth equals its own value** -- its derivative is itself. That self-replicating property makes $e^x$ the backbone of) Tj
T* ( continuous growth, differential equations, and the link between exponentials and the trigonometric waves via Euler's ) Tj
T* (formula.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
