T* (          "difficulty": 5,) Tj
T* (          "sections": [) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "HERO",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "scene": "city",) Tj
T* (                "headline": "Instantaneous Change",) Tj
T* (                "sub": "How fast is something changing at one exact moment? The derivative answers -- by taming a 0/0 ) Tj
T* (with a limit.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONTEXT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Speed at an instant",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "A speedometer shows your speed *right now*, not your average over the trip. But speed is ) Tj
T* (distance over time -- and at a single instant, no time passes. The **derivative** resolves this paradox using limits, ) Tj
T* (giving the exact rate of change at a point. It is the central object of differential calculus.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONCEPT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "The big idea",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "The **derivative** of $f$ at $x$ is the slope of its graph there -- the limit of the slope ) Tj
T* (between $x$ and a nearby point as the gap shrinks to zero:\\n\\n$$f'\(x\) = \\\\lim_{h \\\\to 0} \\\\frac{f\(x+h\) - ) Tj
T* (f\(x\)}{h}.$$\\n\\nIt measures the **instantaneous rate of change**: velocity is the derivative of position; acceleration is) Tj
T* ( the derivative of velocity.\\n\\nThe workhorse is the **power rule**:\\n\\n$$\\\\frac{d}{dx}\\\\,x^{n} = ) Tj
T* (n\\\\,x^{\\\\,n-1}.$$\\n\\nSo $\\\\dfrac{d}{dx}x^2 = 2x$, $\\\\dfrac{d}{dx}x^3 = 3x^2$, and the derivative of a constant is $0$ \(a) Tj
T* ( flat line has no slope\). The derivative of $x$ itself is $1$.\\n\\nReading a derivative: where $f' > 0$ the function ) Tj
T* (rises; where $f' < 0$ it falls; where $f' = 0$ it has a flat spot -- a peak, valley, or plateau.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "WORKED_EXAMPLES",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Worked examples",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "examples": [) Tj
T* (                  {) Tj
T* (                    "title": "Power rule",) Tj
T* (                    "problem": "Differentiate $f\(x\) = x^2$.",) Tj
T* (                    "steps": [) Tj
T* (                      "Bring the power down, subtract one.",) Tj
T* (                      "$2x^{2-1} = 2x$.") Tj
T* (                    ],) Tj
T* (                    "answer": "$f'\(x\) = 2x$.") Tj
T* (                  },) Tj
ET
endstream
