T* (                "markdown": "From the definition, $f'\(x\) = \\\\lim_{h\\\\to0}\\\\dfrac{\(x+h\)^2 - x^2}{h}$. Expand the top: ) Tj
T* ($\(x^2 + 2xh + h^2\) - x^2 = 2xh + h^2$. Divide by $h$: $2x + h$. Now let $h \\\\to 0$: the $h$ vanishes, leaving $2x$. ) Tj
T* (That's the power rule's first case, built straight from the limit -- and every other derivative rule is proved the same ) Tj
T* (patient way.") Tj
