T* (                "headline": "Combine and Conquer",) Tj
T* (                "sub": "A few rules let you differentiate any polynomial -- and, with more, almost any function you'll ) Tj
T* (meet.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONTEXT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Beyond a single power",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Real functions are sums and products of many terms. Rather than returning to the limit each) Tj
T* ( time, calculus gives **rules** that combine known derivatives. Master a handful and you can differentiate any ) Tj
T* (polynomial instantly.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONCEPT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "The big idea",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Building on the power rule, $\\\\dfrac{d}{dx}x^n = nx^{n-1}$:\\n\\n- **Constant multiple:** ) Tj
T* ($\\\\dfrac{d}{dx}\\\\big\(c\\\\,f\(x\)\\\\big\) = c\\\\,f'\(x\)$. A constant factor rides along.\\n- **Sum rule:** $\\\\dfrac{d}{dx}\\\\big\(f) Tj
T* ( + g\\\\big\) = f' + g'$. Differentiate term by term.\\n- **Constant:** the derivative of any constant is $0$.\\n\\nTogether ) Tj
T* (these differentiate any polynomial. For $f\(x\) = 3x^2 + 5x - 4$:\\n\\n$$f'\(x\) = 3\(2x\) + 5\(1\) - 0 = 6x + 5.$$\\n\\nThe ) Tj
T* (**second derivative** $f''\(x\)$ -- the derivative of the derivative -- measures how the rate itself changes \(in motion, ) Tj
T* (that's acceleration\). For more complex functions there are the product, quotient, and chain rules, but the ) Tj
T* (constant-multiple and sum rules already unlock all of polynomial calculus.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "WORKED_EXAMPLES",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Worked examples",) Tj
