T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Composite functions need the **chain rule**: $\\\\dfrac{d}{dx}f\(g\(x\)\) = f'\(g\(x\)\)\\\\cdot g'\(x\)$) Tj
T* ( -- differentiate the outer function, then multiply by the derivative of the inside. For example ) Tj
T* ($\\\\dfrac{d}{dx}\(x^2+1\)^3 = 3\(x^2+1\)^2 \\\\cdot 2x$. The chain rule is the most-used rule in all of calculus, because ) Tj
T* (almost every real function is a composition of simpler ones.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
