(                "sub": "Integration runs differentiation backward -- and, astonishingly, computes the area under any ) Tj
T* (curve.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONTEXT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "From rate back to total",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "If a derivative turns position into velocity, can we go the other way -- from velocity back) Tj
T* ( to distance travelled? Yes: that's **integration**. It both reverses differentiation and measures accumulated ) Tj
T* (quantities -- the area under a curve, the distance from a speed graph, the total from a rate.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONCEPT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "The big idea",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "An **antiderivative** of $f$ is a function $F$ whose derivative is $f$: $F'\(x\) = f\(x\)$. ) Tj
T* (Reversing the power rule:\\n\\n$$\\\\int x^{n}\\\\,dx = \\\\frac{x^{\\\\,n+1}}{n+1} + C \\\\quad \(n \\\\ne -1\).$$\\n\\nAdd one to the ) Tj
T* (power, divide by the new power. The $+C$ is the **constant of integration** -- any constant differentiates to zero, so ) Tj
T* (antiderivatives form a family. For example $\\\\int 2x\\\\,dx = x^2 + C$.\\n\\nThe **definite integral** $\\\\int_a^b f\(x\)\\\\,dx$) Tj
T* ( is the **signed area** under $f$ between $a$ and $b$. The **Fundamental Theorem of Calculus** ties the two ) Tj
T* (together:\\n\\n$$\\\\int_a^b f\(x\)\\\\,dx = F\(b\) - F\(a\),$$\\n\\nwhere $F$ is any antiderivative. So areas -- once found by ) Tj
T* (painstaking limits of rectangles -- collapse to evaluating an antiderivative at two points.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "WORKED_EXAMPLES",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Worked examples",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "examples": [) Tj
T* (                  {) Tj
T* (                    "title": "Antiderivative",) Tj
T* (                    "problem": "Find $\\\\int 2x\\\\,dx$.",) Tj
T* (                    "steps": [) Tj
T* (                      "Reverse the power rule.",) Tj
T* (                      "$x^{2} + C$.") Tj
T* (                    ],) Tj
T* (                    "answer": "$x^2 + C$.") Tj
T* (                  },) Tj
T* (                  {) Tj
T* (                    "title": "Power rule for integrals",) Tj
T* (                    "problem": "Find $\\\\int x^2\\\\,dx$.",) Tj
T* (                    "steps": [) Tj
T* (                      "Add one to the power, divide.",) Tj
T* (                      "$x^3/3 + C$.") Tj
T* (                    ],) Tj
T* (                    "answer": "$\\\\tfrac{x^3}{3} + C$.") Tj
T* (                  },) Tj
T* (                  {) Tj
T* (                    "title": "Definite integral",) Tj
T* (                    "problem": "Evaluate $\\\\int_0^3 2x\\\\,dx$.",) Tj
T* (                    "steps": [) Tj
T* (                      "Antiderivative $x^2$.",) Tj
