(            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONCEPT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "The big idea",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "A **vector** is an ordered list of numbers \(**components**\), often drawn as an arrow. In ) Tj
T* (two dimensions, $\\\\vec v = \(a, b\)$.\\n\\n- **Addition** is componentwise: $\(a_1, b_1\) + \(a_2, b_2\) = \(a_1+a_2,\\\\; ) Tj
T* (b_1+b_2\)$.\\n- **Scalar multiplication** stretches: $k\(a, b\) = \(ka, kb\)$.\\n- The **magnitude** \(length\) comes from the ) Tj
T* (Pythagorean theorem:\\n\\n$$|\\\\vec v| = \\\\sqrt{a^2 + b^2}.$$\\n\\nThe **dot product** combines two vectors into a number: ) Tj
T* ($\(a_1,b_1\)\\\\cdot\(a_2,b_2\) = a_1a_2 + b_1b_2$. It measures how much they point the same way -- zero means ) Tj
T* (**perpendicular**. These few operations, scaled to many dimensions, are all of applied linear algebra.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
