T* (rule generalizes: add componentwise, and $|\\\\vec v| = \\\\sqrt{v_1^2 + \\\\cdots + v_n^2}$. A grayscale image is a vector ) Tj
T* (with one component per pixel; a document can be a vector of word counts. Machine learning lives in spaces of thousands ) Tj
T* (of dimensions, where the dot product still measures similarity exactly as it does for two arrows.") Tj
