T* (                "markdown": "A **matrix** is a rectangular array of numbers with rows and columns. A $2\\\\times2$ matrix ) Tj
T* (is\\n\\n$$A = \\\\begin{pmatrix} a & b \\\\\\\\ c & d \\\\end{pmatrix}.$$\\n\\nOperations:\\n\\n- **Add** matrices of the same shape ) Tj
T* (entrywise.\\n- **Scalar multiply** by multiplying every entry.\\n- **Matrix x vector** transforms the vector: ) Tj
T* ($\\\\begin{pmatrix} a & b \\\\\\\\ c & d \\\\end{pmatrix}\\\\begin{pmatrix} x \\\\\\\\ y \\\\end{pmatrix} = \\\\begin{pmatrix} ax + by ) Tj
T* (\\\\\\\\ cx + dy \\\\end{pmatrix}$.\\n\\nMatrix multiplication chains transformations -- and is **not commutative**: $AB \\\\ne ) Tj
T* (BA$ in general, because doing a rotation then a stretch differs from the reverse. The **identity matrix** ) Tj
T* ($\\\\begin{pmatrix}1&0\\\\\\\\0&1\\\\end{pmatrix}$ leaves every vector unchanged.") Tj
