(                "headline": "One Number, Big Meaning",) Tj
T* (                "sub": "The determinant measures how a matrix scales area -- and whether a system of equations has a ) Tj
T* (unique solution.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONTEXT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "When does a system solve?",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Two linear equations in two unknowns usually meet at a single point -- but sometimes ) Tj
T* (they're parallel \(no solution\) or identical \(infinitely many\). One number, the **determinant**, tells you which case ) Tj
T* (you're in, and it generalizes to systems of any size.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONCEPT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "The big idea",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "For a $2\\\\times2$ matrix $\\\\begin{pmatrix} a & b \\\\\\\\ c & d \\\\end{pmatrix}$, the ) Tj
T* (**determinant** is\\n\\n$$\\\\det = ad - bc.$$\\n\\nGeometrically it's the factor by which the matrix scales area \(and its ) Tj
T* (sign flags a flip\).\\n\\nThe key fact for solving systems:\\n\\n- If $\\\\det \\\\ne 0$, the matrix is **invertible** and the ) Tj
T* (system $A\\\\vec x = \\\\vec b$ has exactly **one** solution.\\n- If $\\\\det = 0$, the rows are proportional -- the equations ) Tj
T* (are parallel or identical, giving **no** solution or **infinitely many**.\\n\\nThis single test scales to $n\\\\times n$ ) Tj
T* (systems, and the determinant also appears in change-of-variables for integrals, cross products, and stability analysis.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "WORKED_EXAMPLES",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Worked examples",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "examples": [) Tj
T* (                  {) Tj
T* (                    "title": "Determinant",) Tj
T* (                    "problem": "Find $\\\\det\\\\begin{pmatrix}3&1\\\\\\\\2&4\\\\end{pmatrix}$.",) Tj
T* (                    "steps": [) Tj
T* (                      "$ad - bc$.",) Tj
T* (                      "$3\\\\cdot4 - 1\\\\cdot2 = 12 - 2$.") Tj
T* (                    ],) Tj
T* (                    "answer": "$\\\\det = 10$.") Tj
T* (                  },) Tj
T* (                  {) Tj
T* (                    "title": "Singular matrix",) Tj
T* (                    "problem": "Find $\\\\det\\\\begin{pmatrix}2&4\\\\\\\\1&2\\\\end{pmatrix}$.",) Tj
T* (                    "steps": [) Tj
T* (                      "$2\\\\cdot2 - 4\\\\cdot1$.",) Tj
T* (                      "$4 - 4 = 0$.") Tj
T* (                    ],) Tj
T* (                    "answer": "$0$ -- no unique solution.") Tj
T* (                  },) Tj
T* (                  {) Tj
T* (                    "title": "Interpret",) Tj
T* (                    "problem": "A system has $\\\\det = 0$. What can you conclude?",) Tj
T* (                    "steps": [) Tj
T* (                      "Not invertible.",) Tj
T* (                      "Parallel or identical lines.") Tj
T* (                    ],) Tj
T* (                    "answer": "No unique solution.") Tj
T* (                  }) Tj
T* (                ]) Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONCEPT_CHECK",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Quick check",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "intro": "Determinant $ad - bc$; nonzero means a unique solution.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "PRACTICE",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Practice problems",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "intro": "Compute determinants and read off solvability.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "DEEPER_DIVE",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Deeper dive: the inverse matrix",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "When $\\\\det \\\\ne 0$, a matrix has an **inverse** $A^{-1}$ that undoes it, so $A\\\\vec x = ) Tj
T* (\\\\vec b$ solves as $\\\\vec x = A^{-1}\\\\vec b$ -- the matrix version of dividing. For $2\\\\times2$, $A^{-1} = ) Tj
T* (\\\\dfrac{1}{\\\\det}\\\\begin{pmatrix} d & -b \\\\\\\\ -c & a \\\\end{pmatrix}$, and the $\\\\dfrac{1}{\\\\det}$ out front is exactly ) Tj
ET
