(              "title": "The big idea",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "A **differential equation \(DE\)** relates a function to its derivatives. For ) Tj
T* (example\\n\\n$$\\\\frac{dy}{dt} = k\\\\,y$$\\n\\nsays 'the rate of change of $y$ is proportional to $y$ itself'.\\n\\nA ) Tj
T* (**solution** is a function that satisfies the equation. Crucially, solutions are **families** of functions; a specific ) Tj
T* (**initial condition** \(a known value at one time\) pins down which one.\\n\\n- The **order** of a DE is the highest ) Tj
T* (derivative it contains. $\\\\dfrac{dy}{dt} = ky$ is first-order; $\\\\dfrac{d^2x}{dt^2} = -\\\\omega^2 x$ is second-order.\\n- ) Tj
T* (To **check** a proposed solution, differentiate it and substitute. For $\\\\dfrac{dy}{dt} = 2y$, try $y = e^{2t}$: its ) Tj
T* (derivative is $2e^{2t} = 2y$. [x]\\n\\nThe leap from algebra is profound: the unknown isn't a number, it's an entire ) Tj
T* (**function**.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "WORKED_EXAMPLES",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Worked examples",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "examples": [) Tj
T* (                  {) Tj
T* (                    "title": "Check a solution",) Tj
T* (                    "problem": "Is $y = e^{2t}$ a solution of $\\\\dfrac{dy}{dt} = 2y$?",) Tj
T* (                    "steps": [) Tj
T* (                      "$dy/dt = 2e^{2t}$.",) Tj
T* (                      "$2y = 2e^{2t}$. They match.") Tj
T* (                    ],) Tj
T* (                    "answer": "Yes.") Tj
T* (                  },) Tj
T* (                  {) Tj
T* (                    "title": "Order",) Tj
T* (                    "problem": "What order is $\\\\dfrac{d^2x}{dt^2} = -x$?",) Tj
T* (                    "steps": [) Tj
T* (                      "Highest derivative is the second.",) Tj
T* (                      "Order 2.") Tj
T* (                    ],) Tj
T* (                    "answer": "Second-order.") Tj
T* (                  },) Tj
T* (                  {) Tj
T* (                    "title": "Family of solutions",) Tj
T* (                    "problem": "Why isn't a DE solution unique?",) Tj
T* (                    "steps": [) Tj
T* (                      "Constants differentiate away.",) Tj
T* (                      "Need an initial condition to fix them.") Tj
T* (                    ],) Tj
T* (                    "answer": "An initial condition selects one solution.") Tj
T* (                  }) Tj
T* (                ]) Tj
