T* (              "title": "Practice problems",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "intro": "Identify order and verify solutions.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "DEEPER_DIVE",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Deeper dive: modeling with DEs",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "The art is translating a sentence into a DE. 'Cooling is proportional to the temperature ) Tj
T* (gap' becomes Newton's law of cooling $\\\\dfrac{dT}{dt} = -k\(T - T_{\\\\text{env}}\)$. 'Population grows but is capped by ) Tj
T* (resources' becomes the logistic equation. Once written, the DE is solved \(by hand or numerically\) and its solution ) Tj
T* (**predicts the future** -- which is exactly how weather, epidemics, and spacecraft trajectories are forecast.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "SUMMARY",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Summary",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "takeaways": [) Tj
T* (                  "A differential equation relates a function to its derivatives.",) Tj
T* (                  "A solution is a function that satisfies it.",) Tj
T* (                  "Solutions come in families; an initial condition picks one.",) Tj
T* (                  "Order = the highest derivative present.",) Tj
T* (                  "Check a solution by differentiating and substituting.") Tj
T* (                ],) Tj
ET
