T* (as $\\\\dfrac{dy}{y} = k\\\\,dt$, then integrate both sides: $\\\\ln|y| = kt + C$. Exponentiating gives $y = e^{kt+C} = y_0 ) Tj
T* (e^{kt}$. This separation technique solves a whole class of first-order DEs -- the workhorse method before you reach the ) Tj
T* (more powerful integrating-factor and transform methods.") Tj
