T* (          "slug": "proof-techniques",) Tj
T* (          "title": "Proof Techniques",) Tj
T* (          "tagline": "Induction and contradiction",) Tj
T* (          "estMinutes": 17,) Tj
T* (          "xpReward": 200,) Tj
T* (          "difficulty": 5,) Tj
T* (          "sections": [) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "HERO",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "scene": "city",) Tj
T* (                "headline": "Certainty, Constructed",) Tj
T* (                "sub": "A proof is an argument so tight no counterexample can exist. Two master techniques carry most of) Tj
T* ( mathematics.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONTEXT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Why proof is the point",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "At the highest level, mathematics isn't computation -- it's **proof**: establishing truth ) Tj
T* (beyond any doubt, for infinitely many cases at once. Two techniques do most of the heavy lifting: **induction** \(for ) Tj
T* (statements about all integers\) and **contradiction** \(assume the opposite and derive an absurdity\).") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "CONCEPT",) Tj
T* (              "title": "The big idea",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "**Mathematical induction** proves a statement $P\(n\)$ for all integers $n \\\\ge 1$ in two ) Tj
T* (steps:\\n\\n1. **Base case:** show $P\(1\)$ is true.\\n2. **Inductive step:** assume $P\(k\)$ \(the hypothesis\) and prove ) Tj
T* ($P\(k+1\)$.\\n\\nThen $P\(n\)$ holds for all $n$ -- like dominoes: the first falls, and each knocks over the next.\\n\\n**Proof ) Tj
T* (by contradiction** proves a statement by assuming its **negation** and deriving an impossibility. The classic: to show ) Tj
T* ($\\\\sqrt2$ is irrational, assume $\\\\sqrt2 = a/b$ in lowest terms and reach a contradiction \(both $a$ and $b$ turn out ) Tj
T* (even\).\\n\\nOther tools include **direct proof** \(chain implications from hypothesis to conclusion\) and **proof by ) Tj
T* (counterexample** \(one example disproves a universal claim\). Mastery of these is what separates doing mathematics from ) Tj
T* (merely using it.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "WORKED_EXAMPLES",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Worked examples",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "examples": [) Tj
T* (                  {) Tj
T* (                    "title": "Induction shape",) Tj
T* (                    "problem": "What two parts does an induction proof need?",) Tj
T* (                    "steps": [) Tj
T* (                      "A base case.",) Tj
T* (                      "An inductive step.") Tj
T* (                    ],) Tj
T* (                    "answer": "Base case and inductive step.") Tj
T* (                  },) Tj
T* (                  {) Tj
T* (                    "title": "Contradiction shape",) Tj
T* (                    "problem": "How does proof by contradiction begin?",) Tj
T* (                    "steps": [) Tj
T* (                      "Assume the statement is false.",) Tj
T* (                      "Derive an impossibility.") Tj
T* (                    ],) Tj
T* (                    "answer": "Assume the negation, reach absurdity.") Tj
T* (                  },) Tj
T* (                  {) Tj
T* (                    "title": "Counterexample",) Tj
T* (                    "problem": "Disprove: 'all primes are odd.'",) Tj
T* (                    "steps": [) Tj
T* (                      "Find one even prime.",) Tj
T* (                      "2 is prime and even.") Tj
T* (                    ],) Tj
T* (                    "answer": "$2$ is a counterexample.") Tj
T* (                  }) Tj
T* (                ]) Tj
ET
endstream
