T* (              "title": "Deeper dive: the limits of proof",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "markdown": "Can every true statement be proved? Astonishingly, no. **G?del's incompleteness theorems** ) Tj
T* (show that any consistent formal system rich enough for arithmetic contains true statements it cannot prove -- and cannot) Tj
T* ( prove its own consistency. This doesn't make mathematics shaky; it reveals that truth outruns provability. It reshaped ) Tj
T* (logic, foundations, and our understanding of what computation and reasoning can ever achieve.") Tj
T* (              }) Tj
T* (            },) Tj
T* (            {) Tj
T* (              "kind": "SUMMARY",) Tj
T* (              "title": "Summary",) Tj
T* (              "content": {) Tj
T* (                "takeaways": [) Tj
T* (                  "A proof establishes truth for all cases, beyond doubt.",) Tj
T* (                  "Induction: prove the base case, then the inductive step.",) Tj
T* (                  "Contradiction: assume the negation, derive an absurdity.",) Tj
T* (                  "One counterexample disproves a universal claim.",) Tj
T* (                  "G?del showed some truths are unprovable within a system.") Tj
T* (                ],) Tj
T* (                "formulas": [) Tj
T* (                  {) Tj
