T* (              "options": [) Tj
T* (                "Base case: for $n=1$, both sides equal 1.",) Tj
T* (                "Assume it holds for $n = k$: $1 + \\\\cdots + k = \\\\dfrac{k\(k+1\)}{2}$.",) Tj
T* (                "Add $\(k+1\)$ to both sides.",) Tj
T* (                "Simplify the right side to $\\\\dfrac{\(k+1\)\(k+2\)}{2}$ -- the formula for $n = k+1$.",) Tj
T* (                "By induction, the formula holds for all $n$.") Tj
T* (              ],) Tj
T* (              "answer": [],) Tj
